review.text: Bestest oldest authentic Chinese food , must go place

Want to have tasty Chinese and Japanese food? Then try FUJIYA in Chanakyapuri, tried hot and sour and corn soup followed by chilly potato, mojito, spring rolls and after that pan fried noodles with gravy. Delicious food was served and the staff was also polite and respectful, amazing experience at this place. Will visit this place again with my friends.

Fujiya is listed in the legendary restaurants of Delhi.It has been here since decades and I had high expectations from this place.They had a vast menu with a lot of dishes.So we decided to order a veg Sushi platter and pan friend noodles. Their pan fried looked very different than the ones I am used to eating.The noodles were fried,more like choupsey and topped with lots of veggies and greens.The sauce of the veggies was bland,some translucent kind of sauce with no flavours just basic salt and pepper.So the noodles were very disappointing.I have had far better pan fried at other places! Next the sushi also couldn’t impress.Tempura sushi was still ok considering the other ones.Other sushi we didn’t took even a second serving after trying it.We unfortunately couldn’t even finish our meals and left!
The food is as chinjabi as possible. It’s just because of the old school feel you can go to the place.
We ordered sushi, fried rice, chili garlic noodles and Hong Kong chicken. Food was pathetic. Completely not worth going. Strictly a NO NO NO NO NO N if u tell them about it , no body bothers.

Lost charm. Very bad experience both in food & service. Had gone with family for lunch. 1. Hot & sour chicken soup was tasteless neither spicy not tasty. 2. Chilli garlic noodles had hardly and garlic & was bland. 3. Prawns in hot garlic sauce was like a below average Indian curry with prawns thrown in it. Horrible taste. When I called manager Thakur he was rude and said it is cooked this way only. Anyways had such a bad experience that wanted to make others aware.
Not a good place for chatore indians. then they have their own order of charging service charge which is a obove the Hon'ble Supreme Court.
Never go there

A lovely restaurant with good ambience. Chilly fish tastes awesome. Must try for all. One of the places to find authentic Chinese soup. I tried Hot&Sour Chicken soup , chili garlic noodles and chicken in hot garlic sauce. Retreat for Chinese people in Delhi 。 。 。 。 。 会 Thumps Up !

Having turned down a couple of times due to a full house, I decided to visit on a Tuesday (when everyone turns vegetarian) evening. Got a warm welcome with a choice of tables even! But in a few minutes, as we were about to dig into our soup, the place was bustling with people waiting outside. So, what’s the fuss all about? It’s the old world feel. It gives you a feeling that it’s been there since ages with a tribe of loyal customers. It’s like nothing has changed and that’s what people love about it. It isn’t cheap by any standards but I guess it’s a great place to grab a beer and munch on an appetiser. A big bottle of Kingfisher is for 300/- . Food: well, it’s nothing special but you can’t fault it. And that’s what brings people back here. You just can’t go wrong. They offer an array of Chinese and Japanese dishes. Some indian dishes quietly slipped in like Gobi Manchurian 😜 I tried the corn and asparagus soup, the chilly baby corn, aromatic pork dumplings, Japanese sticky rice with vegetables. Everything was just right. Right amount of spice, right portion size, fresh ingredients. Quite a homely feel to the place. And the decor coupled with the bustle of the place makes for a good happy outing. Worth a try.

All time favorite place for me to have such a delicious food of my taste. Love this place food with it's vast options cable to fulfill your empty belly. Service is too fast ambience also soo good. Love it Instagram {uid:38945158}

Like the place to have the oriental cuisine. I went to this place with my wife and my daughter. We ordered Chicken Spring Roll: They are crunchy and good option for a starter. Spicy Stir Fry French Beans: Crisp yet not overcooked with the right amount of favoring and went perfectly with the fried rice Zha Jiang noodles: This was the star. Perfect Chinese dish consisting of thick wheat noodles topped with Zhejiang sauce. For drinks, we had virgin Mohito. It was refreshing as it should be. For desserts, We had Brownie zebra: Perfect dessert to satisfy your sweet truth. The service was quick and attentive. I will visit here again.

The ambience of CP’s Berco’s is apparently very appealing. Love the decor. Perfect date place for chinese lovers. I’m a huge fan of their chilli garlic vegetables, the authentic chinese taste. ️ But they really lack in honey chilli potatoes. It either feels too soggy and sweet, or it feels overcooked. I tried it 3 different times but I don’t feel it was a mistake, that is their fixed recipe and it tastes like a sweet dish to me. Service is great here!

I went to cp with my friends fir some party. I saw this outlet of bercos and decided to do a takeaway of some food fir my family. I ordered crispy corn, chilli potatoes, cheese and corn along with a different dish which called sanghai style rice and noodles. Coming to the first, corn were really nice nad crisp with perfect flavours balanced. Chilli potatoes had a nice tangy flavour which made it taste good. Coming to the cheese rolls, they went a little soggy after it was packet but still it was really cheesyyy i must say! , the mixed noodels and too tasted different i would say, ut was something i had never tried before! Overall a nice experience.

1. Ordered Prawn Tom Yum Soup, Black Pepper Chicken Dimsums and Garlic & Cheese Wontons. 2. The Tom Yum Soup was excellent with sufficient prawns and the perfect combination of tangy and spicy. 3. The Chicken Dimsums were great with the Garlic & Cheese Wontons being even better. 4. Orders are served reasonably fast. 5. Pricing could have been a bit more reasonable.

The board looks very basic on the outside, but the restaurant interiors are absolutely amazing 😍. Tried the 'Chicken Tom Kha' and 'Veg Wonton Soup' which were both amazing. Had the 'Honey Chilli Potatoes' sans the honey, which was perfect, crisp and spicy. The only disappointment was the 'Chicken Pan Fried Noodles'. The dish was way too oily and the pan frying wasn't done well, hence the crust wasn't formed perfectly and the noodles weren't as crispy at the bottom. The service was a tad bit too slow and very disorganized. They brought in the appetizer before the soup which was very weird. The pricing was perfect though. So overall, would definitely recommend 👍.

No doubt in excellent staff service. Delicious servings and perfect ambience for dine out with family or couple. Best view at corner tables of stairs (Those who are fond of selfies) It is pocket friendly too. Make sure to order their thai rice bowl (Damn delicious) if you are going for heavy meal. Meal.for 2 in 1000 bucks

Ordered their Three Pepper Bowl which is usually my go to dish. Instead of their noodles, I went for the rice. The only thing I didn’t like about the dish was ‘the quantity of the gravy& Amount of grilled chicken they had put in. I couldn’t complete my rice with it. Had to borrow some spoons of my friend’s Grilled fish in order to eat it all. Though I liked the ambiance, Liked the co-operative staff. 😀
Let the Christmas charm die a Death with Chocolate topping over the Christmas Spirit ✨

If I had to rate just on ambience, I would have given this place 5 star. Such a beautiful place it is. Food is good too but a little bit costly. We ordered Veg Spring Roll and Cold Coffee. Spring Roll tasted good. Not worth the price though. Cold Coffee was okayish. I'll recommend this place just for the look and feel it projects.

Colonel’s Kababz in Defence Colony, New delhi has been doing kebabs and curries since about 25 years now and their quality of food is definitely premium. In the picture: Gosht Seekh Kebab (Colonel’s Special) The kebabs were succulent with amazing mutton blend which is very juicy and moist and the chuntey served along went very well with these but I found the kebabs to be a little overpriced, maybe because of the brand name associated to it, the quantity and presentation could be better. @colonels.kababz @colonels_kababz
Food was good but too much salt in the preli dal tarka. so pls just put less salt. because we can alwz add more but cant redduce the salt pls
Very juicy mutton seekh kabab @colonel kabab defence colonel delhi

Rolls are OVER PRIC3D Rs. 200 and are tasteless. Upon complaining staff said 'we find it Ok'. :/ Menu on tomato has different and lower pricing. The menu given this is attached as a pic. Very bad experience

Although its a old and "Supposedly" a legendary place, tried a Lehsuni Chicken tikka. I Visited the DefCol market itself after ages and really thought of relieving old memories by having their tikka. Unfortunately it was really not upto the taste as it used to be long time back and paying more than 500 bucks for it really hurts.

The Pinner tikka roll was pathetic as it was stale and dry. Paneer was way too hard and it was smelling The green chutney was so bad, it made me puke. It was stinking and had a sour taste. The onions were yellow and stale For 200 rs for a roll, they should at least maintain some hygiene, just because they sit in defence market, doesn’t mean they can sell anything Colonels has rightly lost its charm

I have been to this place once. We ordered chicken tikka roll which was fresh and tasty. In main course we tried Chicken bhayankar which is their speciality. The preparation was good. I liked the quality of chicken they use. The tandoori roti was crispy and the rumali roti was perfectly cooked. Overall I liked their food. The prices are on little higher side. The service is good and quick.

The place is easy to locate but once you get there and order food that is where you start to get disappointed, the sizes of each portion are very small and do not provide enough value for the money that is being paid। Rating: Taste 6/10 Service 6/10 (just because they bring the food till your car) Value for money 2/10

Well this place is overpriced and the food is highly overrated. Spent quite a lot of money for nothing and honestly speaking what’s the price for ? Very very disappointed would suggest people to go to Al Nawaz or other restaurants that are far better than this place. Thank you.

Ever since the seating has been sealed , this outdoor serving restaurant has gone to the dogs and quite literally . From being my favourite go to place for Kebabs ever since I was a kid it has now become a place which has the worst possible service levels and poor hygiene. With barely 3 outdoor high tables ( and about 5 cars in which people drink and eat ) , the serving staff is rude and disrespects patrons . The serving time for orders has increased surprisingly as they are focusing more on the delivery business . A terrible experience . Would not recommend to anyone looking for a pleasant experience .

When I first saw the facade of this place I was awestruck and knew I had to check this place out. After entering I didn't wanted to leave this place anytime soon. The interior is just beautiful. I ordered their "Chilly Garlic Prawns". The presentation was really nice and it was a delight to eat. The flavours were balanced and every flavour was distinct. Really amazing place to chill.

The ambience of this place is too attractive to see. Chilli basil cottage cheese is too good of this place . It had ample of sitting area, which is comfortable too. The staff members of this place take care of each and every need of the customers taste and preference. I liked this place a lot.

I had visited to this place yesterday in the evening to have a delicious food here. The ambience of this place is too good to see. There was polite and alert staff here. Here i had tried: Chilli garlic lotus root Orange chilli prawns Fluffy steamed rice Kung bao chicken All the food stuff was too delectable special the orange chilli prawns. The quality of the food was upto the mark. HIGHLY RECOMMEND
Regular run of the mill buffet food. Taste wise it was OK but not there to beat some good food The drinks with buffet are just one per person which is a let down

I had been to this place with my friends to have some Chinese cuisine. First of all soups and salad varieties was damn good. It has a great ambience. Indoor sitting area is simple fabulous. Staff is very friendly and courteous. Service was prompt. We had ordered Chilli Honey Potato Veg Spring Roll Virgin Mojito and Butter Scotch Ice Cream Shake. All the ice-cream shakes and drinks are outstanding. I really like their menu. I really enjoyed over here with my friends and will definitely keep visiting.

This is a dine-in outlet bar. It serves all kinds of Asian, Thai, Chinese and Sea Food. I recently visited this place and ordered some momos from here. They were utterly delicious😋 The service was good and the ambience was great. The price of the dishes were totally worth the taste. J thoroughly enjoyed myself here and will surely recommend this place to everyone!

Has an amazing tune with friends at this fabulous place. Love the decor, ambience, vibes, food and the staff was courteous. The order was served on time. We ordered Fried rice Kind pao chicken 3 spice chicken chilli honey potato All these dishes are a must try for all the foodies out there📍 Highly recommended , with great decor and really yummy dishes that too at affordable prices❤

This is really good place to have food from the food is really good the taste is yummy the quality is really good to have food was very yummy and delicious the delivery was done on time food was very tasty and delicious the packing was very good and safe had drums of heaven and drunken chicken which was very good to have over all good experience of ordering food from here a must try place

We were looking for a place to visit in the evening a few days ago, then we found this restaurant named Drums of heaven and visited this restaurant. This place is quite famous for it's food. We did lunch here. The food here is very good. Drums of heaven and chillli potatoes are a must try.

Recently visited this place and it was really a great visit. Environment is really healthy and positive. For me it was totally worth it. Staff was really nice. And services are appreciated. And food was very yum and tasty. Ordered: drums soya chilli Hot dragon chicken and honey chilli chicken. And along with them cold coffee. 5/5 to their food. mouth drooling! Highly recommend place!
Nice place. Kind of a vintage feel to it. Dal gosht was nice. Tandoori platter can be tried.

I had my eyes on this place since i was a child roaming the streets of Cannught Place. Finally visited last week. Experience was good. Food tasted average. Nothing to draw myself back. Staff is friendly thought. I liked paneer tikka more than chiken malai tikka. Butter Chicken was debated though - it is not as sweet as some people prefer.

We were shopping at connaught place and were looking to eat at a good place, we spotted embassy and entered. They have a seating capacity of close to 80-90 people on the ground n first floor. A well stocked bar too. We ordered paneer pakodas , masala papad , half butter chicken ,and a few tandoori rotis. Damages to the pocket - Rs 1528 ( US $ 21.4 ) inclusive of all taxes. Overall experience - Rs 650 we paid for half a portion of butter chicken was cut throat , just too expensive and the taste was nothing great. I would rate this place 3 on 5
I have gone with my family ,it wasa great experience and specially the famous daal makani daal I like so much and mushroom was the great ,nice presentation by the staff.
Visited the place for lunch with a friend. We ordered tandoori veg platter, the food was impressive. And the ambience was nice, vintage and fancy.
Cream of tomato soup. Here the beauty is the tomatoes are well well mixed which a wonderful taste of typical tomato soup with cream topping and bread crunch.
Great food and service loved the channa bhatora. Took my foreign clients and they had a great time. Thanks to Mr Pandey and Mr Deepak for giving us a great experience
I love all of its snacks: Big Samosa Large Bread pakora Veg. Hot dog Paneer patty And their mint sauce👌
Please donot waste your money by going to such restaurants. Even after replacing the first one the second one was terrible.

Great place ! lovely food ! Fine dining at Connaught Place . Lip smacking Indian food. We tried the masala papad, paneer pakoda, it was melting in the mouth .butter chicken was great but could have been boneless . Overall a great experience !

FAIYAN - The Chinese restaurant in Middle circle, Connaught Place!❤ . So i visited this place with my family on weekend and I really love the Chinese there. Basically, we were craving for Chinese cusine from very long time and at good location! So we found this one at CP and what could be better than Connaught Place. We had chop suey, fried rice, schezwan noodles and schezwan chilli paneer!🤤 It was a drooling experience for us and we came back home burping and my happy face!😌 Do visit and have some amazing chinese there!😍 We spent around 1200 rupees for 4 people!🤑

Small yet cosy. My favorite was their freshly brewed artisanal coffee. I went looking for something light but filling and got myself some talumein. I think the taste was on point. I wish I could take home their super beautiful crockeries.

Worst part was they don't accept card payments. But cleared the same while placing the order. We ordered Hotn sour soup, pineapple rice and prawn on both the dishes main ingredients was missing (prawns and pineapple) was missing. It was such disaster to went this place. But ambience was good and relaxing. I suggest other place over this restaurant which is far better.

A very small and compact place but food is awesome , you can feel the freshness and aroma of the food very well , potato toastier, chilli garlic noodles , veg manchurian must try, the ice cream they serve is less sugary and simply great, a must visit
The food was tasty with authentic chinese flavours. The staff was courteous and the place was not to noisy, good for an quiet evening time .

Thus is in strict sense a restaurant only , no interiors or things to look at . But wat they believe in is good food n service n m glad to have tried this . Had booked it b4 but I was d only customer , may b the navratre effect ! Talunein soup was really good , d best I ever had , especially for the thin noodles in it . admixed with gentle amount of assorted veggies . D best part is " spring rolls" , I would die for them . So good was the exterior coating , not too thick or thin n no oil coming out n smearing my hands ! Filled with cabbage onion mix , fried to just the optimum level. a must try . , do try the red sauce with it , we used it to garnish our other item tooo. Next up , in main course , American choupsey was nothing like I had in so many Chinese joints ! Liquid veggies tomato sauce came separately with the thin noodles . n u mix n eat , it was simply heaven . a go ahead any day . A hidden gem , but definitely needs to work upon the interiors n the wall paints n old serving glasses !

This spot has the best chinese nourishment in focal delhi. Yummy Chinese nourishment and spending cordial! The amount of nourishment per plate is additionally lovely good.We had Honey Chilly Potato, Hakka Noodle and more. All the nourishment was great and superb and they constantly dazzled me by their food.I love the nourishment here.

This place has the best chinese food in central delhi. I love their prawn noodles a lot. The quantity of food is also good. It is very cosy place with very less tables.I would recommend it to anyone looking to eat authentic chinese in a decent budget.

We went to this place for the first time yesterday for a rakhi dinner. My brother likes chinese food so we did a bit of research before going. The place is a bit small and yesterday being a holiday it was crowded so we had to wait a bit. But once we sat down it was a real treat which followed. We ordered crispy salt and pepper veggies, spring rolls and drums of heaven. Didn't quite like the drums of heaven as it was a bit bland and very dry. The dishes were good. We also had pan fried noodles mixed and fa tuan special fried rice. Portions were great and the taste superb. Even after eating so much we didn't feel stuffed. Food was light and tasty. What we liked most was the similarity in taste with Kolkata Chinese which we miss in Delhi. Service was prompt and efficient. Overall a good experience.
This place serves one of the best dim sums in delhi . Personally in love with their clear soups! Authentic alert! I amma go back their soon!
No chicken, only tofu
Excellent food and huge portions. I have decided to always order from Chungwa for home delivery. Very reasonable too. Thank you Chungwa team
Recently ordered in for 1 portion of chicken talumein soup, and 1 veg talumein. It tastes really nice, but I have had spicier talumein soup from it. Also I found salt to be a little less. :)
Very average food however service is brilliant! I mean too good. for some reason everything just taste same for some reason. I mean its just the same.

cherished the administration and the nourishment was filling. Their segments are extraordinary and I adored the inside. I would prescribe this spot to individuals those things who need to have extraordinary Chinese Food.we requested veg manchurian nippy garlic noodles and seared rice all there were astounding in taste and had a better than average look manchurian was fresh and delicate while noodles however crisp yet were of incredible taste and next singed rice were astonishing had an ideal taste and were cooked appropriately.

Legendary late DC Wong authentic Chinese recipes could be found only at two restaurants in delhi, one at chungwa and Fujiya restaurant at Malcha Marg, Chanakyapuri. I love you guys for being consistent in everything. Loves the foods being ordered. Thubten Khimsar, Malviya Nagar.

I love the food. Food is great! However the service needs to improve. Incase you are still finishing your drink and done with your dinner the waiter might serve the bill and keep on reminding you to pay up.

Poor service, no one to take order. Kept on requesting person to take order. Waited for 20 min only to order. Food was cold, got changed repeat was also cold. Iced tea was syrub. Received each items delayed. Had a very bad experience.

The staff was very bad and not cooperative at all. The chicken was smelling and they were just not ready to accept their mistake.i asked for the manager they were not making me talk to anyone. I can’t believe this type of service. So disappointed I would still expect a call back from the manager so I can actually explain what’s going on in this restaurant.

Visited after long time only to be immensely disappointed! Tried veg wonton soup, chicken in black bean sauce with rice and vegetables in black bean sauce with rice (the meal). Everything was absolutely bland and no taste or texture whatsoever! The prices are relatively high as compared to nearby Asian/Chinese restaurants but the quality was so sad! Never visiting again .
This is a yummy Chinese place where you can satisfy. I am totally love in with vibe of the place. They have some cute crockery and have courteous staff. Must try ︎Chilli chicken ︎hauka noodles

Ichiban is an amazing option when it comes to having lip smacking Chinese and Thai food. This casual dining place serves Chinese, Japanese and Thai cuisine. Place is beautifully done and has warm vibes. Staff is warm and courteous. For appetizers,  I had  honey chilli potato which were crispy with sweet and spicy notes -it will definitely activate your tastebuds. Spring rolls were little oily but tasted good and it paired well with chilly garlic dip. Crispy tangy button mushrooms are definitely worth trying especially for funghi lovers. For main course, I had  Veg manchurian  which was tasty and manchurian balls were soft. Mushroom dimsums were the star dish here.  I would love to recommend it.Thumbs up! Momo lovers should definitely try. I ended my meal with darsan and date pancakes- both these desserts were out of the box and tasted heavenly. Ichiban will certainly hit the spot when you’re looking out for a Chinese meal. Follow my food journey on Instagram- teekhi_mircheee
A great place to have Chinese and Thai food. Easy on your pocket, the service is quick, the staff is courteous and the food is yummy. A must visit for authentic Chinese lovers.
The food is just beyond amazing loved the dumplings, chicken in hot garlic sauce and noodles. The service was on point 😍

Good food, good prices and big portion size. Ichiban has a big menu with something to everyone’s liking and I love the consistency of the food & service. Chilly garlic noodles are my favourite. Being a vegetarian, there are a ton of yummy choices to pick. Paneer satay, spinach and corn are good dishes too.

I love Chinese food with a touch of familiarity and I love the food at Ichiban for the same reason. I have been to this place with my family and we love the food. It’s a cozy restaurant and the food is the real star. The regular stuff like Chilly Chicken, Hakka Noodles, Pad Thai noodles are amazing without being too oily.

There’s something about age old places in Delhi that accentuate the flavours with delicious nostalgia. Ichiban is definitely one such restaurant serving kick ass Asian food, culminated with richness & quality. The menu is vast so it’s hard to pick favourites but I definitely have a few top picks: Chilly Lotus Stem Singapore Prawns Chilly Chicken Pad Thai Noodles They have started doing sushi too which is great. The rolls aren’t overly creamy and are made with fresh seafood. Price point is perfect too cuz portion size is humungous. Check these guys out if you already haven’t. Thank me later.

I use to regularly order soups from ichiban and believe me they are one of the best outlets to try soups from. The prices are okay but the portions are great , a bowl of soup is a meal in itself. Packaging can be improved upon and so is the preparation time.
Nice cozy place for Chinese food. Must have soup here. Quick service. Tasty food. Full filling quantity!
Amazing food, and their service is soo good I mean I usually don’t write reviews but this one deserved one. Its worth the money. Going to be a regular now.

I just loved the ambience and the ethnic south indian setting here. It just complements your meal completely. Food was good too. Their welcome drinks were good. Mysore masala dosa was again something very good. I would highly recommend it. We ordered panchtara uttapam which had 5 different kinds of uttapam most of them were good. Staff was very proffessional and courteous here.
Most authentic south Indian I have ever tasted 😋

Looking for authentic south indian food? This is what we have been missing until now. First experience at Naivedyam and it turned out to be an amazing one. Such courtesy of staff, servers and such a decent crowd. The restaurant takes you to another dimension. Oh the food! Authenticity at its best. Tip- request for gunpowder chutney.

Naivedyam over all 4/5 Best Food - Rasam, Paysam, Sambhar Food tongue tingler - Fried Chilli Ambience - 5/5 Loved the experience and warmth of restaurant special fried chilli is amazing. Paysam that was served with the naivedyam thali was amazing aswell. Will definitely visit again.

We were a group of 13 people and we went to this pure veg South Indian restaurant. We had ordered in bulk, Naivedyam thalis, Mysore masala dosa, paneer masala dosa, Tamarind rice and even Mysore pak. The food is sumptuous and quite filling. The ambience is also very typical South Indian with soothing Carnatic music playing in the background. All in all, this place is a must visit.

This restaurant has become my favourite place for South Indian food! Anyone who loves south Indian food, must visit here! The fast service, quality food, great taste, vintage ambiance & they way they served the food absolutely made me fall in love with this place! I would absolutely rate 10/10 to this place! Must try Mysore masala dosa & Rasam Papad here! Will absolutely recommend to my friends!

Looking for peninsular Indian dish you should visit this place. Even waiter are dressed in South Indian style and they are friendly in nature. Ordered paneer dosa and veg Thali. Both are good taste wise. One should visit if you crave for South Indian dishes

Naivedyam is a good place if you want to have typical south India cuisine. They have the authentic taste. All the food is majorly cooked in coconut oil. They do have a good variety in the menu. Really like their rasam papad and kesari bhaat. Didn't quite like the uttapam and ragi dosa. Service was great! So overall experience - 3.5/5

Food was tasty , fresh.paid almost 300 for the thali - naivedyam thali. they forgot to give kosambari , when I asked about it the guy looked a bit irritated and got me 1tsp of salad in a katori. i feel for this price the food quantity is extremly less especially the rice.
Authentic South Indian flavour and dishes. Must visit. Very warm staff and soothing ambience.

This place is my first love, being a vegetarian it’s hard to find pure veg restaurants that serve food this tasty. It has been at this location since decades and have been maintaining the quality and taste of food without fail. It’s a perfect place for family dinners and is fairly priced as well. I personally love their kababs, paneer tikka, sahi ke kabab and tabdoori pineapple. All of these have a distinct flavour which stands out from other restaurants. Also, their veg thali is something that i order almost always. The dal makhni here is like no other, with perfect spices, consistency and flavour, it is something that you would come back here for, again and again. My mom likes to order masala chaap and paneer lababdaar which is outstanding too. Coming to dessert and drinks, don’t miss their lassi and fruit custard which is absolutely delicious.
I absolutely loved veg Gulati's food it was so good everything was just perfect in taste. staff was so courteous :D had wonderful experience! Good place for vegetarians :D

Veg Gulati:- It was a marvellous experience Going to Veg Gulati restaurant situated in pandara road , ambience was very good there , staff was very courteous and service was very good. Now comes to major part , food that was very good there , especially Malai and Tandoori Chaap , so guys do have a visit to them and try their food.

Went to Veg Gulati with my family friends for a brunch and trust me this place is perfect for all kind of brunch and family dinner. Ambience here is very sober and decent. Talking about the staff, their service was great and on time. We ordered their dahi ke kebab, soyachaap and tandoori mashroom for starter's. Soya chaap were extremely delicious and was very tender in taste. Tandoori mashroom is a highly recommended dish from Gulati- it was well prepared with lots of flavours. In main course we ordered Rajma chawal combo and Mahara thali. My personal favourite dish in main course was Rajma Chawal. In all we had an amazing time here 😊

If you are hard core vegetarian and want to have some delicious vegetarian food, then this is the must visit place. I recently visited this place with my friend and experience here was very amazing. I tried :- > Dahi ke kebab > Galouti kebab * Both were very delicious and has melt in mouth consistency. > I also tried their Maharaja thali - this thali has dal makhani, shahi paneer, diwani handi, rice, raita, dessert and one paratha. The dal makhani and shahi paneer were really delicious. Overall, I really loved this thali and one must should try this 👍 In desserts I had, gulab jamun and ksheeram. Both were supremely delicious 😍 Will definitely visit this place again for sure 👍

Now Pandara Road has a lot of restaurants but when it comes to vegetarian food, veg gulati stands the best in my eyes. I recently went there with a friend of mine and loved the place to bits. I started with a Tandoori platter and a kebab platter and both the platters are to die for. Grilled pineapple, mushrooms, dahi ke kebabs were the best out of both the platters. Further, they have a huge menu with lots of variety of main course dishes. I had Dal Makhani, Veg Biryani , Soya Rara and Palak Kofta and all of them were delicious. If you are coming here don't forget to try their chaap/soya preparations because they are to die for. Palak Kofta is a must try from my side. You can end the meal with ksheeram which is made with carrot, bottle gaurd and almonds. To be honest, bottle gaurd might not sound too appetizing but this dessert was absolutely delicious. (Highly recommended!) I would definitely love to visit the place again for its awesome food. ♥️

Except for the food (which too was not great guns), nothing was anything better than GROSS. Their staff head came to take the order n guess what he din even know all the items in the platter. Having been tasted the famous Hyderabadi Biriyani from their counterpart in Secunderabad outlet in the recent past, I found this experience not so satisfying. The portion size was average and is in no match to the quantity served in Paradise outlets in Telengana. Moreover, the Nizami Mutton Biriyani also tasted quite different as far as my food memory from Secunderabad Paradise is concerned. The spice quotient was much lower, perhaps toned down to match with the taste buds of the Bengal region, but compromised with the authenticity of the dish as served in the Telengana region. Although the Nizami Mutton Biriyani tasted good, the Royal one was a complete let down for its blunt taste. Kebabs (comes in a platter of 8 pieces) were succulent and tasty, but the sizes were small compared to their pricing. However, the Qubani ka Meetha was enjoyable and the sweetness index was perfect to linger on the mouth as a sweet aftertaste. Staff were extremely courteous and attempted every bit to address the needs of the customers on a busy day. As a food lover, my humble suggestion to the authority would be to seriously look into the portion sizes as it stands in no match with their original counterparts in Telengana. P.S:- The ambience of the place was in sync with their original counterpart where you can enjoy the food in complete harmony with others instead of a private kind of dining experience.

Nawabi Mutton Biriyani - (5/5) Priced at Rs.381, this was the showstopper. It is supposed to serve 2 people and comes with 4 pieces of mutton, accompanied with curd, sambar & onions. Unlike the original Paradise Hyderabadi Biriyani, the spice quotient is toned down to match the Kolkata palate and the result is really good. Highly recommended. Nawabi Chicken Biriyani - (3.5) Priced at Rs.381, this was a letdown after the mutton biriyani. The rice was more bland than the mutton biriyani. However the 2 chicken pieces given were very nice with the flavours intact inside, as is absent in most other biriyani joints, where one gets bland chicken pieces. However, avoid Chicken biriyani and go for Mutton. Qubani ka Meetha - (0/5) A dessert made out of stewed apricots. Similar to chutney. The texture was runny and bland. Double ka Meetha - (1.5/5) Fried bread pudding with saffron. Similar to Shahi Tukra. Despite the food being very good (however you can easily skip the kebabs & dessert, just go for the biriyani), the service was horrible. Very poor crowd management. The waiting line was not managed properly. The washroom was very dirty. Nawabi Biriyani which is supposed to serve 2 people was sufficient for only 1 person. Mutton biriyani got over at 9pm and had to order chicken biriyani after that. They closed the restaurant at 9:30 pm whereas it is supposed to be open till 11pm. The food scene in Kolkata is a tough one and Paradise has to really buck up in terms of service in order to compete with the other biriyani joints. A lot of other customers had the same complaints as us. Was not at all impressed with service. Hoping for their speedy improvement.

Satisfy your Oriental cravings @ PETUK Jadavpur.! Spreading its wings from Hazra to Jadavpur, PETUK is all set to cater to the tastebuds with its economically ranged oriental rendezvous. Regarded as one of the best oriental hubs in this city, the food served here is in no way inferior in taste or flavor, when compared to some of the big shot names in this city. The very fact that the pricing here is low, is again in no way indicative of the fact of the quality of the food which is served here and in a way is definitely a misnomer. If you were to walk 2-3 mins straight from the Tollygunge Auto Stand at Jadavpur, making you way right past Hindustan Sweets and towards UCO Bank, PETUK would fall on your right. The outlet here is minimally sized, and would probably accommodate 15 heads at the max. We started off by customizing ourselves a MOMO platter, which had a mix of 2 Chicken Steamed Momos, 2 Chicken Fried Momos and 2 Chicken Pan Fried Momos. The Steamed Momos were some of the best in town, and so were the Pan Fried Momos. The sauce was what made the most difference, apart from the taste and flavorful filling inside. Next to come were Fish Fry, Crispy Chicken and Pan-Fried Fish in Chilli Mustard Sauce. Fish Fry and Fish Finger is definitely what PETUK is known for, and rightfully so, the Fish Fry was fingerlicking good, retaining the quality and quantity set by its HAZRA counterpart. The Fish Fry had beautiful layering of Kasundi or Mustard Sauce, along with a thick layer of the boneless fillet of fish. The crunch of the exterior, the flavor from the middle, all you would perhaps need more are some onions and a little bit more of that mustard sauce. Crispy Chicken too faired well, with the boneless strips of chicken being tossed in a sweet and tangy sauce. The Chicken was crispy and crunchy, and the sauce left a long aftermark in the tastebuds. Pan Fried Fish in Chilli Mustard Sauce was perhaps the best of the starter, with the kickness from the chillies and the tanginess from the mustard getting infused within the delicate flavor of the fish. For the maincourse, we tried Burnt Garlic Fried Rice, whose aroma and flavor made us spellbound. A perfect accompaniment to this was the Chicken Manchurian, something we loved relishing here. Both the quantity and quality was more than expected and hence was a good value for money. #oriental #chinese #starter #maincourse #fishfry #fishfinger #PETUK #Hazra #Jadavpur #PETUKHazra #PETUKJadavpur #whenstomachtickles

It is hard to pass by the Welcome Restaurant in the bylanes of Fort in Mumbai; this iconic restaurant was established in 1924. Surely, the offerings have morphed over the years; I hope that some of its original traits have survived the onslaught of the changing culture and demographics of the metropolis. This was one time when I was aimlessly walking by this crowded street in the Fort area and chanced upon this eatery. The place is clean and well organized. It has all the characteristics of the typical Udupi restaurant, except that its interiors had this middle era charm (as in not quite contemporary). Ambiance gets a thumbs up. Since my visit was to quickly check out the place, I ordered three bellwether items: Steamed Idli, Upma and Filter Coffee. The Steamed Idli was the hero – the idli was hot and the sambar was also piping hot; the chutney tasted fresh. The Upma was a different story: one the one side, it had those welcome tomatoes and peas but the consistency and the texture of the upma were disappointing. It was not the expected warm somewhat molten consistency, it was tepid and dry. The sambar and the chutney were unable to resurrect this fallen warrior. The coffee did not taste anything like filter coffee – it was inexorably sweet and had all the look and feel and taste of instant coffee - that was a bummer! The Idli was the last man standing. Just for that, food gets a thumbs up. Service was courteous and attentive. For the time I was there, there was a changing of the guard (as in wait person); it was seamless. The sequencing of the service was remarkable. This was one of those rare instances when Service made an attempt to make up for the food performance. Service gets an unmistakable thumbs up. Like most of the old era eateries, the South Indian restaurants are being ravaged by the unforgiving palates of the changing demographics. In their attempt to survive, these establishments are resorting to want to be all things to all palates. The result ends up in the broadest imaginable spectrum of cuisines - a midstream world of confused identity. If only these restaurants would stick to their core competencies, I am sure, at a minimum, they would have an identity – which, hopefully, will reflect in the economics. Overall, my experience was okay, not exhilarating. The hero was the Idli. Yes, I would go back for the Idli, should I find myself in the area.

I was at the Royal Garden Resort for a family picnic a two days back. we were a group of 33. and v did end up with a pretty good deal of 600 per head for entry to the water park + breakfast + lunch + hi tea with snacks + popcorn, ice gola, pizza and pasta free all day + dashing car + ice cream coupon. I shall review the food part of it over here. The food starting with breakfast was pretty good. there was Idli Sambhar, Upma, Papdi Gathiya and Jalebi along with tea and coffee. all of it was decent. In lunch we were served 3 vegetables available in both jain n regular- Chole, a Paneer sabzi(paneer tikka i suppose) and one more that i didnt try. it was accompanied by kachori and dhoklas in appetizers, Basundi and Gulab Jamuns in sweets, Puri n mini Parathas in breads, Dal Fry and Rice and salads and papad. lunch was amazing too. basundi was though a bit too liquidy but no compromise on taste. For Hi-tea they served Pav Bhaji, Fried Rice and Manchurian along with tea and coffee. i didnt try Pav Bhaji. but fried rice and manchurian being jain lacked a bit on authentic indo-chinese taste because garlic isnt used in jain. but still it was decent. Pizza n Pasta were ultimate. and the fact that you could have unlimited(only 2 pieces at a time, go again in line for more :P ) only added to the joy. the pizza was a regular veggie pizza with usual toppings of a pizza gravy,tomatoes, bell peppers, onions and cheese. the pasta was jain but still amazing. it was arabietta pasta the red one. Popcorns and ice golas were free too all day. although both only in one flavour- salted and kala khata respectively. Icecream to some point disappointed as it was a small 5rs cup of vanilla. to some extent its due to soo much they gave us otherwise that we expected a better icecream!🙈 Overall from food perspective if you are at the resort you are sorted. the water park too is pretty good with many slides, wave pool and comparatively cleaner waters. PS- Sorry for lack of food pics as I kept my phone in the locker since we were heading for the pool!

We did enjoy the breakfast, the egg bhurjee was surprisingly good in taste and enough for two. Ambience: nice place for kids. It is really large and there is ample of resting place. They could have done better with the small garden located at the entrance. The swings and slides need repair. Rooms: We booked the Super deluxe and I would say that there are a lot of things that disappointed and could have been better. 1. Not enough plugs to charge the phone and none near the bed. 2. The toilet didnt have tissue paper. 3. The TV could have been larger screen with better volume 4. They don't provide a remote for the AC so it is either too cold or it is not. 5. The mini-fridge was only started when we entered so it took ages to cool. Common sense was lacking here. 6. The bedsheets had stains if you understand the kind of stains I am talking about . Please hire a better laundry service. Overall, the water park is great but too much crowd on weekends. If you enjoy constantly bumping into people everywhere, then do visit cause it is still value for money if you plan only a day trip. I did not appreciate that the guards did not allow me to park my bike inside the premises even though there was place and even after I told them politely that I had a room booking, they did not relent. The reception had to intervene and allow me parking. I feel your rooms are over-priced and would be value for money if you allowed access to the swimming pool and park for a few hours after 6 pm once the day trip crowds leave for the day OR atleast provide complementary food like lunch or breakfast or both. Even if you have to close the water park, give access to one of the swimming pools for the people who book your expensive rooms. Overall good water park, room service but don't plan a stay.

Hilton International Airport Hotel in Mumbai invited us to celebrate their Oktoberfest promotion (on till the 15th of October) as a precursor to the launch of their open-air grill section: The Brasserie Grill  As a part of the night, we got to sample a platter of grilled meats, cold cuts and a few pints of off the shelf beer. What we ate: 1) Beer Basted New Zealand Lamb Skewers- Roasted peppers and lamb skewers. Can't really go wrong, can you? The lamb was soft and well-cooked while the roasted peppers added a sweet heat to the food. A nice combination that worked well. 2) Lamb Chops and Gravy: A nice, soft, pink lamb chop served on the bone with a peppery gravy to add depth of flavour and a moreish spice to the dish. The lamb was complemented by the roasted potato served that brought out the texture of the lamb and the spice of the sauce a lot more. The only drawback was that the chops served were cooked differently. One was medium while the other was a lot more on the medium-rare side. 3) German Sausages: Subtlety smoked sausages done on an open grill that paired surprisingly well with the cold brews. Nothing too fancy, just a nice sausage that gave us the tiniest of tastes of Germany! 4) Grilled chicken in Mediterranean spices: Now we love a good chicken leg and we were happy with the soft/tender texture and the strong spicy flavour as well.  5) Cold Cuts of Meat: A selection of pork and chicken cuts with marinated olives that were a nice wrap-up with our last pints of beers. The pepper pork was the highlight of the selection. Overall, the evening was pleasant thanks to the ambience (outdoor seating by the poolside). We just wish there were more vegetarian options because there was only one option which seemed lacking, and we're surprised to find only Indian bottled/draft beers on the selection of beverages for what was a celebration of Oktoberfest. On the other hand, if you are hardcore non-vegetarian and fond of beer (they did also have a table for beer pong) you will have a good time.

The Brasserie Grill is back with a bang with their Oktoberfest from 3rd October to 15th October 2019. It's an open-air grill set up outside the Brasserie restaurant at Hilton. We were invited to the Pre-opening of the Oktoberfest event and love their hospitality. Beer and food were simply wow. If you love beer and grill this one is a must-try. They have three different options available 1⃣Mumbai October Heat - Beer butter-basted New Zealand lamb skewers, Chicken Roulade, grilled croquettes, roasted cherry tomatoes, roasted Pumpkin, and peppers. 2⃣German Sausages – Smoked Sausage, Bavarian sausage, roasted onion and peppers 3⃣Home Made – Platter of grilled meats and fish / Assorted grilled veg platter. Each of these options is served with two draught /pint beer and is priced at ₹1290+ Tax per person (only for the Oktoberfest) So do visit them before 15th October 2019 and enjoy this amazing experience of great Beer, good food, fun games, perfect music and more.

Came to Marche for a birthday and overall it was a great experience! We sat in a little alcove off to the side of the main room which felt nice and private, although the whole venue had a great relaxed atmosphere with everyone absorbed in their own groups. The main room is for board games which is $15 pp for 3 hours and includes any drink off the menu (ranging from $4-$8). Be aware that this is an alcohol free zone! There is also a heap of private karaoke rooms around the back. We are not board game experts by any means but they seemed to have a good selection of party games like exploding kittens, cards against humanity, heads up, and lots of Catan! Food wise it’s Taiwanese street food with quite an expansive menu covering dumplings, bao, rice bowls and fried food. Food is well priced at about $10-$14 for a single dish and $21-$24 for the fried platters. Drinks are a range of cute milk teas, sparkling sodas and mocktails. Would have no problem eating here again! The only downside is service which was slow and pretty disorganised. Not sure why but they only have one iPad for payment at the front of the store which creates a huge bottleneck of people wanting to pay and leave as well as coming in to get seated. If you keep your expectations about service low and stay patient you will enjoy Marche!

Came here several times and enjoyed it! The food here is good, from the noodle, very tasty, good portion and well cooked. All the deep fried stuffs, yumm, i wished they haven’t changed the menu, cuz I loveddd the set with sweet potato, popcorn chicken, tofu and sausage ️

A place where you can play board games, sing karaoke and eat Asian style snacks, including the all important bubble tea. what a brilliant idea! We weren't sure what to expect when we walked in to this joint, but it was a truly lovely experience. It had a nice and relaxing vibe. They had a wide variety of board games and who can say no to karaoke? Our drinks were well made and the pearls were up to scratch. We had a small tray of fried goodies to top off the night. Needless to say, we will be marching back to Marche in the near future!

Interesting concept. Did not try their food but had a matcha latte which was made perfectly. Not too sweet with enough green tea. Enjoyed the boardgames but thought the entry price was a little too much.

Love this place! We have been here many times and always had a great time. They have wide selection of boardgames to choose from. You can also ask the friendly staff to explain the games, if you want to learn it quick. The food here are mainly finger food but there are also actual meals for the hungry. Food is good, bubble tea is great, staff is amazing!

I tried pork belly rice bowl yesterday. It was good, the portion is a bit less than i expected but it still fine. The mocktail was not bad as well. Good palce to hangout with your friends with the boardgame that only $15 pp for 3 hrs, and the food is nice too.
Didn’t even get to play a board game but the food was great, the atmosphere was great and the staff were great! Definitely a unique experience worth repeating!

We have come here many times and it is a favourite place to bring friends and visitors. Yes, it is a little dear at $12pp (with 1 drink included), however, you would pay that to go to the cinemas or do something else for a couple of hours so I think it is worth it. Also, it feels like a cosy cafe, not some cheap, dirty den of boardgamers. I would definitely ring ahead and book because it was really busy the last time we went. *Just to be clear, the high rating is for the whole experience, not the food.*
So delicious! The Vietnamese chicken salad at Bluebag is absolutely incredible, I could eat it all day. Beware the lines are very long, and you should allow 10-15 minutes during busy times. Yum!
This place does great chicken curry and pulled pork. The salad bar is always busy. The only criticism is that the orders can get a bit mixed up during busy times, however the food is great.

I was walking past Blue Bag and saw the hordes of people inside and outside lining up. What is going on here I thought to myself. After battling with myself about whether I could bothered lining up (cause frankly I was frozen and over winter) I decided to see what all the fuss was about. Surprisingly, despite the millions of the people in there, I was served very quickly and only waited a couple of minutes for my food. I was shocked. What an efficient system they must have. I decided to try the BBQ pulled pork with brown rice and side salad lunch deal for $9.90. This was quite a large portion and I struggled to finish it. The pulled pork was tasty, loved the healthier option of brown rice. The salad however needed some dressing. Too plain for me. Although I suppose you can mix it with the pork. I also noticed they served St Ali coffee so decided to try this. It was ok but not as good as some of the surrounding outlets in Freshwater Place. Based on today's experience, I would come back and try some of the other menu items like soups and salads.

I visited blue bag for a simple work lunch. I ordered the bbq pulled pork lunch special. The restaurant itself was not very large but there was ample seating during the lunch hour and the food itself was tasty and reasonably priced.

St Ali coffee? Yes please. This place offers a really good price of $3.5 for small and a large for $4. Best of all it's buy 4 get the 5th free whereas other places you'd get the 10th free. Taste? Not bad but one more slight shot of coffee would be great. They offer 20c discount for BYO cups and service sandwiches and healthy soups.
The salads are excellent. Friendly staff. And above all else, great coffee to look forward to when getting through the painful work day! Thanks lovely ladies!!!!!!

Fresh, healthy everyday lunching needs. They serve hot and cold food - soups, wraps, sandwiches, salads and some special hot food with healthier options like brown rice, couscous. Today i tried their lamb tagine lunchbox special, which came with lamb and chickpea tagine, couscous and a side of salad. I was pretty happy with the flavours, quantity and ingredient qualities. The amount of lamb was good, not too much couscous, salad was mostly coleslaw with dill and some other leaves. I can see myself coming here again.

This place is a convenient healthy store for quick on the go lunches with freshly made and packaged sandwiches and salads. The food is quite nice however it's is extremely expensive for what you get. A standard club sandwich is $8+ There are plenty of cheap and similar alternatives around including woollies and other stores selling fresh sandwiches or even subway two shops away. It does have a nice clean feel to the store with its blue and natural themes and minimalistic design. It's a nice shop but it's just very pricey for what it offers.

This is my favourite lunchtime eating hotspot. Just like it's big cousin Pret A Manger in London, this store has an vast range of breakfast, lunch and even healthy dinner options. Whether you want sandwiches, rolls, wraps or salads they have it all with a great selection and whether you want rye, white or wholemeal bread, they cater for all tastes. My absolute favourite is the piping hot Mozzarella toastie (with a heavenly combination of pesto, tomatoes and mozzarella cheese), it is a burst of flavour in your mouth and is perfect on a cold Melbourne day.

Great lil place across the rd from my workplace that sells sandwiches and wraps with different fillings. They all look very fresh and you can either get the full serving or half serving (50cent extra or so) which helps when you are indecisive! Their smoothies are really tasty too. I think i mango and pineapple one was my fav! Mmm.

We came here after failing to grab a table at our preferred restaurant. It was cold out, what better way to warm yourself up than to have some hearty Korean food. My friend and I shared a couple of dishes. We had their mustard chicken topped with a generous amount of spring onions. The boneless chicken pieces was slightly crisp but the mustard sauce could have been more potent. Served with a side of salad. We also had their sundubu jjigae which at first glance was severely lacking in chilli powder. The other components were fine (wouldn't have minded some enoki mushrooms) but the broth was quite bland without the chilli component. For a place that's called Spicy Korea, I expected much more. I usually find Korean food in general pretty consistent but was slightly disappointed during this visit. It was quite full and perhaps there was a hiccup or two. Judging from the patrons they work nearby and frequent this establishment quite often.

Fast and efficient service. The original fried chicken was cooked to a good level of tenderness. Many places tend to overcooked their fried chicken. The bibimbap was also yummy. Would come back go try other dishes!

I was craving for fried chicken so I ordered the meal. Unfortunately it was not the typical korean fried chicken. It was more like diced/chicken pieces fried with flour. It wasn’t bad but i think the batter could be crispier. I had the soy fried chicken and probably wouldnt order that flavour again, flavour was more mild, a bit boring to my liking. I have to say the portion is massive for $12.50 meal. I wish the salad come with sesame dressing instead of mayo. Haha obviously I am so used to Nene chicken. I will come back though to try other things.

I ordered the spicy pork bulgogi and spring onion and mustard chicken - both were quite good. However the rice they served was clearly a mix of old, dried out rice and some newer, more fresh rice. I pointed this out yet was re-served the same stale and inedible rice which ruined enjoyment of the meal.

Their food is always tasty and fairly priced so we keep going back. But once we tried their sundupu, we decided to not go back for a while as it tasted really fishy. I get that it was a seafood tofu soup but it was overpowering. My beef bulgogi was superb, their salad too.
Was seriously impressed by both meals. The chicken fried rice was full of flavour and omg the kfc perfect!!!

Original fried chicken is my favorite one. I've try soy and sweet and sour one. Trust me, you can't go wrong with the original. It's good with rice and salad also kimchi. Cheers! Don't forget beer or soju.

I had lunch today at spicy Korea . Apparently it is always very busy for lunch time. However , service is good and quick . I had pork fried dumplings and a spicy kimchi fried rice with pork . Both delicious . They also always serve a mini salad seasoning with a kind of yogurt sauce . Simply amazing . I’ll be back . 100% recommended .

My review disappeared so im reposting. Good food. Horrible service. I havent eaten here in a long time so i had no idea they changed to self service, bcus almost a yr ago i always ate here and i wasnt self service before. The very rude waitress told me to find my own seat rudely. And told me to get my own cup, again rudely bc she said its self servce, which i have no problem with. The problem was the way she said it, and lastly, she gossiped abt me to her coworker. and looked at me weirdly. Im not a diva. Self service isnt a problem. If only she said it nicely. Like a decent waitress would to a random customer who user to love that resto.

Went there for lunch and ordered the fish katsu It came with a simple salad and bowl of rice (ok for $18) But half the fish was thin and dry the other thicker fillets but raw Couldn’t eat more than half of the dish

This little cafe is good. I haven’t been here in a while but it’s still hits the mark. The service is alright, efficient with out being too friendly. That was ok, it was early in the morning (8am) and I guess we were all waking up haha My strong skinny latte had some nice milk froth and the coffee flavour waa tasty. This place is still worth a visit.

Used to really love this place. They have now changed their name to Mr Ashcroft and changed the menu slightly. Service has gone down hill and coffee just tastes awful! The guy who took my order only wrote down “Soy”, not flat white or latte or anything else. Probably just make them all the same. Also don’t ask you for your name anymore, which used to be a nice personal touch. Used to get a coffee from here every morning but now have to search for a new go to coffee place. Very disappointing.
Excellent Cafe in the heart of the CBD. Coffee is the best in the city!

Nice little corner café with sustainability in mind. At first sip, the milk is noticeably thin and the consistency is watery. The coffee is more on the darker roast side with flavours of tobacco and cereal. There’s a small menu with coffee pairing foods – pastries, sandwiches, sliders, etc all looking very fresh.

On the corner of Bank Place and Little Collins is a very unassuming and small little café that you could be forgiven for thinking it was part of one of it’s neighbouring, larger establishments. But walk in and you can see that they have a little kitchen and coffee area. It may be small, but what they lack in size they make up for in quality. The Dear Luncher is a big fan of their coffee, but the other day there was also a sandwich consumed and it was excellent. It was a rare beef with pickles and slaw on sourdough combination. The only downside was that it probably should have been cut in half. The Dear Luncher likey Lt. Colin long time.
My regular cafe near work. Friendly people with a relaxed atmosphere. Note - the food looks delicious but I haven't tried it. The 4.5 is for the coffee only.

A positive early morning experience to start my day! Lovely healthy breaky & expertly made almond chai. Best of all though is the warm vibes, beautiful/vogue decor, music that transported me somewhere else & authentic happy staff. Thank you
A beautiful little place to stumble upon in the early morning. All smiles in what seemed like the perfect escape in the midst of a busy CBD. My coffee was wonderful.
Great spot for a morning catch up with friends and have a good coffee.   The smashed avo and feta is amazing in this great little cafe.
Great little spot for lunch on a sunny day. I loved the Thai soup, and the sandwiches they make. Fantastic spot to chill out from the office in Historical Bank Place.
This cute cafe was found during my lunch break and apparently was opened for a few years now. The coffee tasted a bit different to normal coffee beans but was a really nice flavour. I loved it.

It sometimes sad to see things change, just like my now ex-favourite coffee shop in the city. The service is great but that’s all. My previous review back in 2016 was a 5/5. But my most recent coffee was one of the worst that I’ve had! Full stop! I asked and paid for a small strong skinny latte. But what I got was a milky flat white that was soo bad I wanted to take it back but I didn’t have time. The cup was soo full the coffee spilt all over my hand as I was standing still! Yep! I understand that the cafe was busy but this was just awful. Overall there are some amazing cafes in the CBD so I’d recommend going elsewhere. May 2016 I've been coming here for ages now. It's always great service and great coffee no matter how busy it gets. I love the fact that they give you a glass of mineral water too. This is my favourite coffee shop in the CBD.
Ordered cold drip (Mandheling, Indonesia). Has an amazing juicy sweet flavour with notes of blackcurrant, orange, and 🍏. Love it 😍
Good coffee (I'm hard to please so good is actually good!), relaxing atmosphere, reasonable waiting time and outstanding service - will be returning!
I love this place! Amazing coffee, chai and matcha. Staff are lovely and the ambience is fab. So busy on weekday mornings though! Love the outdoor seating

Disappointing & very overrated. Waiting in line for a takeaway coffee for more than 5 minutes is not acceptable when there’s so many other options around. Particularly, when the cafe prioritises phone coffee orders (ie from firms in the Rialto) ahead of those customers in the actual cafe. Need to re-think how they deal with demand or buy another coffee machine.

Although a classy little set-up, their drinks menu is really lacking in quality. Overtime, I have tried a variety of their coffees, chai lattes, matcha lattes and hot chocolates. All were largely bland and lacking any depth in flavour. Drinks were not hot enough, lacking in creamy-ness/milky-ness when needed. Such a shame.

Stopped by this coffee shop on a morning, located next to the Rialto tower this little coffee shop was busy and full of people waiting. the decor was nice they had a board with headline news articles which patrons can read whilst waiting. the coffee it self was a bit watered down and could have used an extra shot.

This coffee shop melds in perfectly with the building's facade, on the inside it's got a character of its own. A select few pages of the newspaper is displayed so you can enjoy your coffee standing or take a seat and enjoy the upbeat music blaring in the background. We grab a table and immediately a pitcher of sparkling water arrives to our table, very nice touch. Soon after my latte which was just generally well rounded. Smooth, not overly strong or weak and a great foam to coffee ratio. I was impressed by my friend's cold drip which came with a crafted block of ice. Other than coffee they have other little treats but it's all about the coffee. Loving all the minor details, that's another one for the books.

I go here frequently for coffee on my way to work. Sometimes there is a long line in the mornings but it moves quickly and you are never waiting too long for your coffee. The best part is the free sparkling water that is not only on tap but offered to you personally whilst you wait to pick up your coffee. I take soy milk - they don't use Bonsoy here but they use a brand called 'Soy Boy', which tastes just as good (the only soy milk I have found thus far that I will drink happily aside from Bonsoy). Definitely recommend.

Berry, yoghurt and chia muffin was really nice at this place. Although I was wondering whether they put the wrong tag up as I think there were chunks of pear in it, which was really nice. The blueberries were really big and moist too. The whole muffin was great - no boring bits! I'm sorry for the half eaten muffin photo, I totally forgot to take a photo of my actual muffin until I started chomping it.
If you are after amazing and delicious salads for lunch, give EARL a go. The ultra green salad is the best! Super fresh food and the staff are lovely!

Cafe providing healthier food and coffee . hhhmmmmm. The last time I check, coffee is still regarded as poison by some in the medical field . just check the copy paste at the bottom . Anyway, who listen to these medical experts anyway, we go where the good coffee brewed. You need to look hard for this place hidden in the middle of St Kilda Road concrete jungle. I didn't try their "healthier" food range, but I did try their coffee; Soylatte, above average and well made. "The health effects of coffee are quite controversial. Depending on who you ask, it is either a super healthy beverage or incredibly harmful. But despite what you may have heard, there are actually plenty of good things to be said about coffee. For example, it is high in antioxidants and linked to a reduced risk of many diseases. However… it also contains caffeine, a stimulant that can cause problems in some people and disrupt sleep" authoritynutrition.com/coffee-good-or-bad/

Decided to try this joint out today for lunch- healthy canteen near macdonald and subway. A Lot of options for bfast and lunch. I decided to go with the brown rice, chicken and veggie salad in ginger sauce. It was ok - brown rice was a bit hard but then figured since its a cold salad. Didnt realised taste the ginger though which was a shame. Overall still good. Service was efficient.

So grateful for Earl Canteen to have arrived on St Kilda Road as there are so many less than inspiring places to eat along the soulless corporate strip. I LOVE their Fancy Fridays and cannot look past their pork belly sandwich - it fills me up for the rest of the day and is the perfect treat to celebrate the arrival of FriYay. Make sure you also order the dark chocolate, sea salt and walnut cookie along with anything else you get - regret will not be experienced.

Good variety of sandwiches and salads. Love their Mac & cheese toasted sandwiches, and salted chocolate chip cookies! Great coffee, and they usually have almond milk available if you don't do dairy. Very friendly staff too.

Great place for a morning coffee fix. Awesome cookies and muffins made on premises. Same goes for sandwiches, although on the expensive side they deliver plenty wiling quality ingredients and punchy filings! Good work Earl!

caption.text: Toasted ham, cheese and tomato sandwich

review.text: Blink and you'll miss it. No signage outside, look for the glass doors. I thoroughly enjoyed my toasted ham, cheese and tomato sandwich and coffee. So many cafes don't toast sandwiches properly. This one was toasted all the way through, piping hot with gooey cheese. Coffee was great too. I also liked the look of the pastries and sweets.

3.5/5 This is a cafe on Collins Street in a beautiful old facade of a building at the front. The service was alright, and efficient. The service was friendly and quick. My strong skinny latte coffee flavour was good but it was burning hot making it impossible to drink! I'm going to have to ask for a non extra hot coffee in future.

[Coffee Review] Called into Howitt House today for a take away coffee. Staff were very friendly and seemed to know many of their customers which was a good sign. I ordered an strong almond milk latte and it was unfortunately a little bit meh. Not that strong and not that creamy. Probably wouldn’t come back for their almond milk offerings KD
Greeted by friendly staff and we ordered two lattes which arrived quickly. The coffee was hot and tastey. The place itself wasn't too busy which made for an enjoyable coffee. {uid:37790627}

I am a huge fan of the guys at Howitt House. They are super friendly and build great rapport with customers. I really like their bacon and egg brioche, although the coffee is not as creamy as I like it to be

Had one of the moist amazing banana bread, nice and moist & only $4. Heaps of other sweets like, choc brownie, pastries, carrot cakes. great selection.  Coffee was delicious also. Highly recommend if close by.

Great espresso bar located just in the foyer of 1 Collins st. Flat white was really tasty, fast & efficient service too. Coffee by dukes coffee roasters. Cool looking spaceship coffee machine also, highly recommend when up paris end of the city.
Under new management and have automatically improved the food & coffee offering. Coffee is by dukes coffee roasters. Would def come back. Fast speedy service & great staff!
There is a great atmosphere at Signature Coffee, the staff are incredibly friendly and helpful. Blown away by the quality of the food and the excellent service.

I cannot rate these guys highly enough! Been in there twice now, the first time they went above and beyond when the batista was outside having a coffee, noticed my hands were really full of other stuff, went inside, grabbed me a carry bag and held my coffee while I reorganised myself haha. Then my next visit, once again I was greeted as I walked in and the lady remembered me, and my order, even though there was days in between my visits. I was extremely impressed. Their customer service is incredible and they also have the coffee to match. Thanks for a consistent, immaculate experience guys :)

I called in here for a pre dinner drink. This pub has a shingle saying “Happy Hour” 5pm - 7pm daily. Ok cool I’ll grab a pint. When I asked the barman which beer was their happy hour beer he looked at me blank and asked a female and male colleague. Do we have happy hour? I was told that all the tap beers were happy hour beers which was pretty cool. Ahem! So I ordered a Mountain Goat Steam Ale. That’d be $12.20 mate. Sorry I asked for the happy hour beer I said. Yes they’re all happy hour beers on tap. When I finished my beer I went back to the bar and asked a different barman of my beer was actually a happy hour beer. I was given a spiel about how CUB own all the pubs and well this is the city mate, things are more expensive. My ears were bleeding with this! It’s quite sad as I’ve been going to this pub off n on for a long time now. For the record, there’s a lot of pubs and bars with happy hour drinks/beers available in the city. Even non CUB craft beers like I had recently.

Love this place. Been here over the space of 20 years. Lots of great people having fun and an old mate used to be the ass/man. But god. Do the some of the security just come in to protect their friends or what? Got accused of pushing a security guard. A person I had literally never seen before and had to leave. Fine! So if you want to have a few games of pool and then get kicked out for no reason this is the place for you! And if management shall take the shallow act and state that I was inebriated. How the hell am I writing this about 40 minutes after I left? I have no problem leaving a negative review even though it’s a great place! Go there. Meet some awesome people!

I was early for a foodie event nearby so called into the Exford to escape the heat. This is the sort of pub you don’t see too often these days in Melbourne. I can remember when places like this were on every block . a quiet old school establishment where you can drink a pint with your mates. and not need to talk over the music . you might not even need to talk at all really. When I turned up it was missing any women whatsoever. just blokes having drinks after work. I ordered a pint of Yaks Pacific whereas I probably should have gone the Carlton. it felt like a Carlton sort of place. Pool tables and a couple of screens for the sport. Pizza advertised at $8 all day everyday or $11 including a pot. I love these old venues. and they are so few and far between. I hear this place gets rowdy in the late evening but today it was just a mellow pint 🍺

Such a fun place! Definitely come here for their comedy night! Go upstairs and buy some drinks from the bartender! He is awesome! I ordered a Long Island Ice Tea and he hadn't made one for a while. It tasted so good! It was very strong too. Also it was only $15! $15 for a Long Island Ice Tea is amazing! After that I got him to choose the cocktails he wanted to make and he made lots of different drinks! Would come back for the drinks definitely. The downstairs $8 pizzas are okay. Not much toppings but still tasty.

I honestly don't remember much about the beer prices or food quality or whatever because the atmosphere was so hostile and it made me extremely uncomfortable to be there. This is one of the most pro-white bogan places I've ever set foot in (which is kind of funny since Exford Hotel is in the middle of Chinatown). It feels like everyone there is a biker or otherwise tough in some way. When I was there with some friends (I'm Chinese, one of my friends is Indian), we were getting dirty looks from a lot of the other patrons and it was just not a nice feeling. Our white friend didn't care about all the stink eye we were getting but the glares made it very hard for my Indian friend and me to enjoy our drinks or have a carefree conversation. If I were white, I'd probably like the place. The music they play is what I like to listen to (rock, metal, grunge, classic rock, you get the idea) and I would interpret the atmosphere as super down-to-earth, no bull, a bit rough-and-tumble, and if that's your thing, go for it. Just bring loads of white friends with you if you're not white yourself.

I love the no frills vibe of the place, its awesome & come back regularly. Great residency music & pizza excellent value - however the attitude of the female staff member needs a readjustment. Rude is an understatement. If you dont want to be at work - stay home, you're in a customer service role!

i usually just go there for the razzmatazz indie disco every second saturday night, and its the best dancing experience one could ever have.  the djs will play your requestswithin reason, and the bar staff are cool.  i would not know what to do with myself if this place or the ding dong lounge closed down.  having said that none of my friends like it so most of the people i know there are the people that i met there or the bar staff.

Usually get a footlong with chicken fillet and salad when I'm super hungry but I just wanted a snack today so got two cookies - chocolate chip and white chocolate macadamia. The cookies were not as gooey and chewy as other places.

I eat from this place often. Didn't know i had to take the punching card otherwise I would have got some free ones by now. :P Eating here is cheaper than the nearby alternatives , especially since you get more fillings as well as sauces. The staff is also good .
Got coconut juice freshly cut from a young coconut here so it was very refreshing and surprisingly a large drink inside. Loved it! But the hot food or cold options weren't too appealing.
I decided to order a schnitzel from here as I was starving and it was so dry! I couldn’t get through half of the chicken , price wise it was average
Looks so delicious but the taste is so bad. The chicken is only 2 mm thick, more flour than the chicken. Lucky I only bought one. Never want to try this again

Was craving for some cheese pie after a long day of having fun at the casino. Found this place in the food court area and they have 'cheese pie' which doesn't look like pie at all. The taste was okay but was quite expensive for the value of the food ($7.90). However, the cheese was a lot and I'm happy with it.

Stereotypical food Court Food. Roast was decent, the meat was cooked well, however, didn’t appear consistent throughout. Service was not too long, but not really my idea of friendly. Staff member looked preoccupied with something or someone else. That said, for a quick decent portion it did the job.

Food court steak sandwich done pretty decently. Served quickly with only a short wait while the sandwich was freshly prepared. Sandwich was a good size, generous filling of steak, caramelised onion, mushroom and greens. Tasty and flavoursome. Chips were a bit of a miss. Happy with the meal, perhaps skip the chips next time.

Wow this is overpriced! My salad of chicken & quinoa and Asian beef tasted good but set me back $14. I had also bought a falafel wrap for $12 which was real bad - the wrap was so thick and tough with barely any filling.

Terrible food, won't go again, beef is a like a wood, and selection is very in appealing, had to run so I decide to go with this one and regretted it from the moment I receive my dish. Absolutely not again.
Food was soo good and services also. I and aunty like pork and beef here, really tasty so happy that we bought food from this shop, thanks a lot.

Worse customer service I have ever experienced in Melbourne. Do not ever go there! Shocking especially from such a nice location based in Crown. I sent back an overcooked poached egg and young waitress (Chinese girl) gave an absolute horrible black face and argued back that poached eggs are meant to be overcooked. I mean how hard can it be getting another egg recooked? She did not apologize what so ever and took the plate back to the kitchen without explaining the problem to the chef. I waited for another 15 minutes to realized that she did not ask the kitchen to remake the egg.
