Had to speak to the manager who call me bluff for saying I left the plate on the counter and left without explaining what was wrong with the food. Pretty dumb thing to say especially when I have already paid for the food and my husband has finished his breakfast by then. Manager tried to give me a form of lecturing the whole time while young waitress was standing behind him fighting back my comments and yelling out that "I didn't cook the egg". Well, that pretty much sums up everything about the customer service. Young waitress clearly is incapable of handling customer complains tactfully (or understanding Australian consumer rights) and has caused a big kerfuffle with a paying customer. The manager was as worst not apologizing and having a go at me while allowing the staff to mouth off at the back. The waitress should be let go. This would have never happened in a proper cafe with trained staff especially in Australian hospitality. Big disappointment indeed. Demand for a refund and left. Will definitely pass on the feedback to everyone I know.

My score 3.75 stars (avge of 2 reviews). J and I had late lunch here at about 2.45pm on Fri 27th Sep. Service was ok. Not huge queues to order, but food took a little while, so at least partially made from scratch. Our food selection was much better this time, but still trying to find the sweet spot. Home made lemon iced tea ($3.00) - Refreshing, a little sweet with rich lemony and mild green tea flavour.  Chicken katsu curry on rice (instead of noodles - large $12.90) – Reasonable amount of crumbed chicken strips, crumb quite well done but chicken moist. Ok sushi rice, lots of curry sauce which was quite nice. Onion, capsicum, 2 pieces large carrot (not too firm). Reasonably filling serve Grilled tofu steak (large $11.50) - 1.5 tofu steaks (were a slightly odd texture), pickled radish, sushi rice, corn, black sesame seeds, nori strips, red onion and very generous amount of crisp mixed lettuce. Overall, a bit dry as all the sweet teriyaki sauce was at the bottom. Matcha waffle cone ($2.50) - Nice crunchy green cone. Soft serve had a pleasant matcha taste and not too sweet. Cheap! Dec 2018. Service nice. Meals a bit of a let-down and at $35.30 didn't seem great value. Lemon iced tea (refreshing).  Grilled tofu and mushroom bento - Veg croquette > underwhelming. Tofu and mushroom > ok but lacked flavour intensity. Edamame > ok.    Tempura fish bento - Crumbed scallop > ok, prob needed some sauce. Yakitori chicken > small but tasty and quite nice. Fish > 3 small pieces, quite nice, but more like FandC's than tempura (and mayo was average). Both bentos also had: 1 Gyoza > ok but overcooked and wrapper a bit dry. Green salad/Coleslaw/Wakame salad/SMALL charred corn/Rice/Few pickles > All ok.   Afterwards we had a Black sesame soft serve in black waffle cone. It looked great and had a nice nutty/sesame flavour, but was a bit too sweet for us (Matcha better IMO).

We were feeling hungry but didn’t want something too filling so we shared a chicken Karaage bowl between the 2 of us. Honestly the food here isn’t bad. The serving size was pretty decent and the Karaage was quite nice. I liked the spicy mayo sauce. A good option in the food court!
Good value for lunch.
Chicken Katsu is excellent!
My son's fave! :)
Tasty food for the price! Highly recommend
We had ramen noodles and the ramen noodles were nice and hot. Yummy!
Absolutely delicious. The choice of rices and udons and the toppings are wonderful.
Super convenient to where I work! And the food tastes really good in comparison with the price
Fast service, freshly prepared and the quantity is large so it’s bound to make you full for a decent price :)
Thought we'd try it quicky before the movies. Staff were friendly. The Japanese pancake awesome and both our dishes were done well. Couldn't fault

I'm not entirely sure what to say here but im shocked angry upset i ordered teriyaki chicken look at what i got! honestly this is disgusting everything else was fine but if this is coming out of the kitchen when they're hand made theres something wrong!
Sushi was fresh and very good. Nothing extraordinary but no issues either. Prefer this one to the other sushi place at knox. Prices are good/reasonable too.
The best Teriyaki chicken I have ever tasted. I have no idea how they make the chicken so tender and juicy. They are amazing. And the service is great too.

The ramen was weird. Didn't feel great after eating it. My friend had the pork Katsu curry which he enjoyed although he would've liked more curry sauce. Waiting time was also quite long (20 mins) which doesn't help that we went there for our lunch break.

Had the chicken teriyaki and it was crap. I actually thought they had given me beef as the chicken was weird looking. The chicken was flavourless and had to spit out about 5 bits from gristle or fat, nowhere near enough sauce and ended up leaving 70% of the rice as there was no sauce. Steer clear

Came here yesterday for lunch . Lots of food from okonomiaki to ramen maybe that’s why nothing is good. I tried the pork ramen but it was katsu ramen which is very weird and just changed the whole ramen experience. Food was tasteless and if I was not hungry I would not eat it.

My work friend and I ate here for lunch. My friend was very disappointed with his salmon salad. It had too much dressing and the salmon was dry and tasted and looked like it had been fried. He also had some scallop ball things but unfortunately they didn't taste or look like scallops. Instead they looked like crapstick meat. My ramen was ok. It was a cheap $9 something ramen. Still not the worst ramen that I have had in the area. The broth didn't contain much flavour. I would like Tokyo Sushi to have a spicy ramen option. The dumplings were pre-cooked and were cold and tasted not very fresh. I would only recommend Tokyo Sushi if you were looking for very cheap ramen.

Had a few diff hot food items here. Not bad for a fast quick takeaway option. Prices are good. Quick services. Always busy. Curry is nice! Great amount of spice. Rice paper rolls were kinda small - 3 for $6.50. Sauce that came w it was bit plain and watery? Overall good lunch joint.
Really poor ramen. Worst ever. Plastic bowl, plastic spoon. No flavour in the soup, a waste of money and food. Never go to Tokyo sushi kitchen again.
Got a takeaway teriyaki salmon bento box. Salmon was dry and pretty lifeless. Salad to go with was miniscule and dry. Tempura was meh. Miso soup was miso soup. Wouldn't go back.

Yo-art has some great fro-yo flavours, however the consistency of them could be much thicker, in order to make the yoghurt better. The toppings are great, however there is a lack of sauces/syrups. Overall, good fro-yo joint.

Came here while checking out northland and after sussing out Preston. The fro-yo was nice, they had a decent range of flavours some fruity and some creamy with heaps of toppings. The big let down was that the seating area was filthy, half finished cups everywhere, used napkins and dirty furniture.

caption.text: Chickpea quinoa mix salad excellent value...

review.text: I always love chicken and avocado sandwich and this is one of the places I always get it from. My food are always fresh and awesome. Not to mention their coffees which are extra special than other coffees 😊 Great customer service as well. Very friendly staffs 🖤
Best Salad to fast food place rather than Asian and junk food in the mall. This place is much better than the Greek outlet and SUMO salads. Freshly made stuff. Highly recommended.
It was one of the worst coffees I have ever had. It was very bitter and disappointing paying $4 for a coffee that is not very nice. Zouki needs to lift their game.

Absolutely overpriced, which isn't too bad if the food isn't bad. It was disgusting. The bread tasted like the sandwich was made the previous day, and the salad tasted like it was prepped days (read "multiple") earlier. Not only that, you can go over the road to the Lazy Cat cafe and get fresher, TASTIER, and cheaper. My first and last time buying from the overpriced Zouki @

Their sushi rolls are pretty good, better than their Bento boxes. However if you are willing to travel, Sushi monger has much better sushi and better price too. Used to love their miso soup, so tasty and generous size too, however the recent ones I had were watered down version, very disappointing, won't order it again.

Always come here whenever I need something quick during lunch breaks. Very fast service all the time and friendly staff. There's a lot of different sushi and they're all fresh. Prices are not too expensive too.

Nice friendly staff and overall good fresh sushi. The service is always great (even during busy lunch hours) and it's a very convenient place beside my workplace. I come here frequently and am never let down by the variety.

Today my quick takeaway lunch came from the closest Japanese place to work. Sushi Land has a lot of fresh, vibrant looking sushi, sashmi and hand rolls on offer. I grabbed my usual “Salmon Pack” and was not disappointed, this little venue always delivers on freshness and is quick with the service. Today I also grabbed the miso soup and I must say I enjoyed it more than the last time, it seemed to have a little more substance and flavour, not at all overpowering in any sense. KD

Your typical run of the mill Asian-run Japanese sushi place that is a bit meh. Had the chicken teriyaki roll and it was extremely salty, no balance in flavour and the whole thing kinda fell apart as you bite into it.

Tried Sushi Land for lunch today. It's a busy little restaurant with very limited seating and a dated feel. I tried the spicy chicken, teriyaki chicken and cooked tuna brown rice rolls. They were all pretty good, although I did notice that the seaweed was a bit hard. The sushi is reasonably priced so it's worth a visit - but you're probably better off getting your sushi "to go".

It is surprising how hard it can be to find brown rice sushi, even in the CBD - this place does a spicy salmon and avodaco brown rice roll which gets me through the weeks - if they're out of what you like they make them fresh for you and do good deals at the end of the day

I enjoy eating here because they offer unique spicy flavoured sushi, my favourite being the spicy chicken. The brown rice is also a must try. The rice and fish is always fresh. The service is always friendly and professional. Don't be worried by their long queues because their service is very quick and you'll get your Sushi in no time.
We came here for dessert and we were not disappointed. The dessert was very pretty and I almost didn’t want to eat it and ruin it. They use a lot of fresh raspberries which was worth the price.

We had a pre theatre booking was one of the first at the restaurant. To be sitting within one of the most iconic buildings in the world and able to wine and dine is something to be savoured. Every dish that we ordered was presented by a different wait staff and components explained. The sourdough was crunchy. I had the noodle dish for entree which comprised of a pho like noodle (rice) and an egg noodle. Flavours came through the delicate sweet camerlised sauce. All the components of the dish worked to give it pop and taste. The presentation as you can see was superb. The duck was next and the cooking techniques were executed perfectly. Presentation again was A1 and it didn’t want to stick the knife in the ruin the work of of perfection. Hand made Iced Vo Vo S gave it a nice Aussie touch at the end. Service was friendly and efficient. Always special dining here in a special place!

Enjoyed the big night out menu, great menu and dishes and I added a cheese course, the service staff were great with looking after all the guests. Can't wait to try the other dinning options and menus here

I think I may have managed to not dine, even once, during Guillaume Brahimi’s 12 years running the Bennelong restaurant at the Sydney Opera House, though I believe that I did dine there once, a few years before that, perhaps not long after my arrival in Sydney in 1999! I remember reading that it’s a difficult venue to run, something about the way the kitchen is located and the shape of the place, never originally intended as a restaurant (I think). In any case, I’d been reading about Bennelong under Peter Gilmore for the last few years, and how it’s been a huge success, and so what an amazing place to help a dear friend, Andrew, to celebrate his 50th birthday!
Cured and cultured menu is awesome! We added a couple of extra dishes ontop of the chefs selection to share and had plenty of food.

Wow wow wow what an amazing experience. First time dining and certainly won’t be the last. This is now my top choice to take visitors. We decided to eat bar side in order to share food. So beautifully prepared in front of your eyes. The stand out for me were the ocean trout ceviche and the lamington. The service is the best I’ve had in Sydney. The whole experience was Truely out of this world amazing.

My first time dining at the Sydney Opera House was a delightful experience. I ordered a passionfruit mocktail, the wagyu tartare, confit duck and chocolate dessert. The passionfruit mocktail was very sweet and I would probably not order it again next time. The tartare had so many different textures and was a very balanced dish. Although I enjoyed the duck and its' packets of flavour, I would recommend them to have more green vegetables. If I hadn't had a vegetable side dish to go with it, it would have been too heavy and salty. The last dish out of the 3 course meal was my favourite. Chocolate literally "across the water" from the other side of the harbour - the ganache melted the chocolate dish, the crumb gave it texture and the chocolate mousse was smooth.  The food was exquisite and deserved 5/5 stars. My only concern was that once the sun had set, the inside was very dim. I could not even see the beautifully presented dishes. More lighting would make the dining experience perfect! Food: 9.5/10 Ambience: 9/10 Service: 9/10
It was beautiful. Staffs are friendly.

My boyfriend took us here for my birthday dinner. The waiter we had was really non attentive and she just didn't look like she cared to be there. I asked for what was popular and recommended and she just said 'anything'. When I asked for popular cocktails recommendations she had to read each one from the menu. She didn't actually know the menu at all. You get a 2 hour seating however it took 1 and a half hours for our mains to come and the waitstaff kept saying that the kitchen was busy but other tables that came AFTER we ordered got their food before us. For such a fine establishment this is truly disappointing service. The only thing I enjoyed was the dessert. Very upsetting. Our meal cost us $400 for 2 people and the waiter brought us a bill for a quarter of that. Had we not brought it up to them she wouldn't have even known.

My boyfriend took me there for my birthday and it was amazing! Although you only have 2 hours to stay but I think it was enough for 3 course. There was not much to choose on the menu but I recommend the pork chop and confit Duck for your main! By the way, they provide unlimited Sonoma breads so even the size for the food was not enough you can have the bread as much as you want. It’s definitely a great experience to dine in there. And you must book it earlier because they are quite busy.

When you hate crowds so you get to the markets before 5am, you need coffee asap! Always open when we turn up and whilst I don't often get a piccolo, hubs always gets either an almond chai or a soy mocha, which we have all enjoyed. It's decent enough. After our market haul we decided on breakfast. I got the BLAT which came as you would expect and was yum.

What a great start to a slow Saturday morning. Excellent coffee and even more excellent morning breakfast. The eggs benny is something I would come for every Saturday to the cafe. Certainly will be a regular visited. Highly recommend this place.

After an early morning market shop, escaped the hustle and bustle of Sydney Markets to have a bite to eat at the Plaza Cafe just across the outdoor car park towards Parramatta Road. Fast, friendly service and tasty wrap which was nice lightly toasted.
Morrocan lamb sausage roll is delicious. Great coffee. Have almond milk. Fast friendly service. Always busy, patrons voting with their feet.

For a outer suburb local for certain people this place punches above its weight. It has good points and bad points Of you stick to the menu, you'll have no problem, once you alter or ask for something of normal you're in for a difficult time and a let down
Highly recommend. Coffee was amazing and great service, made me feel very welcome. I tried the eggs benedict and it was delicious! Will definitely be coming back

Plaza Café has had a makeover and is serving the best food in the area! The food is so fresh and beautifully made. I found them on Facebook and thought to give them a try! Big breakfast was delicious and the coffee is excellent. Highly recommended!

Celebrated my birthday at the Sydney Tower 360. My boyfriend booked us the Platinum set menu, staff were very kind and helpful. I have required a appetiser other than the oyster and the communication was very good. Also had them recommended a glass of red to match with the red, it was perfect. Overall the view was really good and the foods were also spot on. Definitely worth a visit for both the food and the stunning night view.

Most disgusting overpriced shit ever. Actually so gross. $140 per person without drinks is trash for the food served. Oysters were disgusting, food was under seasoned. Staff were really nice and helpful and the view was good but not worth it overall. Maybe try the buffet instead and see how it goes

I would say food was yummy and the view was spectacular. However, for a day that’s not busy nor packed, the service is incredibly slow. Experience: we arrived at 12:36pm and been given a butter but the bread didn’t arrive till 1:10pm (coz we couldnt wait any longer and we just asked for it). Our mains has not been served til 2pm. But cheers to fabio for doing a good job tho!
No.

Back in November 2018, my partner and I visited 360 Bar and Dining located in the Sydney Tower in the middle of the CBD. So this post is slightly overdue. However, it was such a great experience that I feel I should still write about it. I just hope that I don’t miss any details. I know that I have forgotten some of the food that was ordered but the pictures should hopefully make up for this.

Great view as you would expect the ambience is upmarket and relaxed. The wait staff were attentive and seemed to be at our table when we needed them. Perfect service. Ordering from the set menu we started with oysters and scollops. The oysters came with a foam and i don’t recommend the foam it should not be on the plate or anywhere near food. The scollops where nice but would have been better if served with the row. Mains were duck and fish. Both dishes looked amazing and kudos to the guy in the kitchen plating. He’s doing a amazing job but unfortunately both the main dishes where not to our taste. The food was fresh and all that but our palates were not a big fan. The deserts were okay nothing to rave about.

We had a lovely time up in the clouds! The staff were knowledgable with the food and were very attentive to our needs. We felt very pampered. The food tasted incredible and had very good portion sizes. Sadly we didn't have enough room for dessert which we really looked forward to! We had the shared antipasti and steak with side veggies for our mains. Booking was easy, and we had a good table by the window. The lift, as a precaution to those suffering from claustrophobia, is tiny. So you might wanna prepare yourselves for that. All in all, we will definitely be back for another date night.
The view and the experience was amazing. However, food wise. not so great. The cod and spanned dish tasted really boring. However the desert was great.

We came here for our anniversary and you cannot fault the food and the view. It was raining all afternoon, but it was still breathtaking. The only issue I had here was the service. It started off wonderful, until we got our mains. After we had finished, we waited about 40 minutes until our plates were cleared. That was fine, as we enjoyed the view, but it honestly felt like the staff had forgotten us. We had arrived with another couple at the same time, and that couple left at least 40 minutes before we did. I was also told that because we were celebrating our anniversary here, we would be provided with a complimentary chocolate anniversary plate. Which we did not receive. After we finished with dessert, we waited about 20 minutes as we waited for our plates to be cleared and to pay the bill. None of that happened so we just went up to pay the bill at the bar. All in all, great food, great wine. But the service wasn’t the greatest. For what we paid, I experienced better service at other restaurants for the same price.
Really fresh and delicious food, lovely charcuterie as well. All around a great experience with lovely wait staff. Would definitely recommend for a special occasion.

A client meeting took me to the Fire Station Cafe on a recent sunny Thursday morning. A brief glance around the pleasant courtyard at the rear of the venue suggested this was the case for the majority at the clientele. I had a (passable) Chai Latte and my companion a skinny cappuccino which he finished so was presumably acceptable to his palate. A reasonable option for a caffeine top-up if you found yourself in this neck of the woods. Don't expect to see it featuring on Instagram any time soon though.

I used to work in the building that joins onto this cafe, and went there once or twice a week. I love this place! There is a bit of a wait for takeaway at lunch time as many workers come here for lunch but it's worth it. Their wraps are huge, and the vegetarian nachos are easily the best nachos I've ever had. They always have a different soup of the day too, I love the minestrone, pumpkin soup and the zucchini and bacon. Perfect for winter. The owner is super nice. I miss this place!

Great bfast and value for $. We went to Bill's eater say in surely hills, while a nice breakfast the price reflected the place to be seen, fire station was as good a break fast but the price was unbeatable value, highly recommended

This cafe makes the best coffee this side of Pitt street. Ive been getting my coffee from here for over 4 yrs and its been consistenly the same.The service is fast and efficent. i have to say, it also helps that the owner is a hottie with a cheeky smile thats also pretty consistent!
My New favorite Cafe. Next time your in the city, You must stop here for lunch. The lentil & Chickpea burger with mayo & Sweet chilli sauce is the best in the world!

This place is an over priced tourist trap - some places you go and you think it will be small but turns out spacious. this is the opposite- food is pretty much what you would eat at a local RSL club. Chinese tourist fight over prawns . the only decent thing is the dessert. And for some reason the A/C sucks.

Such a great atmosphere, very romantic date night - delicious seafood, and the desserts were amazing. Not sure if other negative reviews were unlucky with their experience but we were very happy. Would definitely return.

Some of the previous reviews are rather unfair, we think. We came for the view and for that the experience delivers in spades. The view from all sides of the dining area is magnificent. We thought the buffet was ok. Some decent seafood, some decent other dishes, some reasonable desserts. We’ve had better buffets and we’ve had worse. This is no gourmet experience and not was that what we expected. It’s reasonable food for the money. The complimentary sparkling was good. Our coffee was excellent. Our server was new and he did a great job. Yes, it could be better, but we still enjoyed the experience.
While the view is good, the food quality is poor for the price you pay, and I'm usually easy to please with food. Disappointing, has so much potential, not a good look for foreign visitors

Paid top dollars for 'quality' open buffet. Food was absolutely disgusting. The seafood was cold and like rubber. The deserts felt like I was chewing on plastic. The so cold rotating tower stopped turning. All in all 1/10 experience. Waste of money.

The amount of choices they had offer for food, was not a lot. There was only three hot food stations and a cold bar with the tiniest mussels I had ever seen, and a dessert section, that was okay, food was average, and I managed to try to fill myself up with dumplings and French fries. I didn’t appreciate, right as we were seated someone came over to take photos, and when we ordered drinks, it was super hard to get the attention of the waiters, and some of them were just standing at the till. I don’t really understand why they stationed their food in such odd places, since it’s 360, if the food is facing on the opposite of the place, you would need to walk all the way round to get the food. The atmosphere was good, but you’re just paying for the view.

Booked in advance, still didn’t get a window seat Very loud! Don’t eat here if you have even the slightest motion sickness, it will make you want to chuck up your food. Wait staff are friendly however seem to be short staffed, spent a long time waiting to pay for the tab. Food was very mediocre and there wasn’t a large selection available, the seafood tasted as if it was caught 2 months ago and left out for just as long, tasted defrosted and old. The view was nice however you can’t really take any photos because of the glare from the windows. Would definitely not recommend to anyone!

Thanks for all your comments, folks. As the director in charge of corporate entertainment for an extremely large and respected Aussie blue-chip company, I was considering the Sydney Tower as a venue for around 50 important overseas clients (or their representatives) when we recently brought them all to Australia for a familiarisation tour. My budget for the four day event was A$1million so I had a few options to choose from. Having never been to the tower restaurant before I assumed it was an iconic Aussie venue that would be perfect for entertaining our guests. Fortunately, reading all your reviews convinced me this would probably have been the worst place to come. I spoke to my boss about it and we both agreed it would probably cause the company irreparable harm. We ended up taking our 50 visitors to one of the high-end hotels, just to be safe. A big pity, though, that something that should be an icon for Australian tourism is so badly managed and reviewed. Please allow me to apologise to all overseas visitors that have had a bad experience at the Sydney Tower - hopefully you appreciate the bad food and poor service does not reflect Australia as a whole. Unfortunately most Sydney residents have no idea just how bad it is because 99% have never been (and never will!). Thank you folks again - you probably saved my job!
Amazing view on top of the city, perfect for a romantic dinner. Their buffet is well stocked with a variety of food from all the world, who satisfy all the taste.

Quite possibly the worst food I have had in a very long time. The first thing that hits you when you walk in is the smell - terrible! The restaurant looks and feels dirty. It’s basically a feeding factory with a wide choice of unappealing and bland dishes. Great view, but it’s just not nice in anyway. Disappointing and expensive tourist trap. Spend your precious money elsewhere.

Water grill is now a good $6 to $8 above value. Burgers for 24-26, Pizzas above $25, meat hits $30 at least and seafood starts at a whopping $29 fish and chips. If it delivered highest quality, we would be looking at good value. Pricing generally good fare at these prices, with decidedly average Pizza (average dough and and not so Pizza lamb Pizza), average chips and over-battered and sometimes over cooked fish and chips (no real brown malt vinegar in sight), we are simply looking at “pay per view dining”. The fish platter is good but overpriced at $135 as well. A return to reality and improved basics at decent prices is in order. I nearly do not want to order food here anymore simply because value and money are very far apart by now. Great place but needs to come back down.

I came to Watergrill on a Sunday night to celebrate my grandmothers birthday. Food: I ordered the slow cooked pork pappardelle and my fiancée ordered the king prawn salad. My meal was very yummy - pork was flavoursome and tender and the pasta was al dente, just how I like it. The sauce was balanced and sweet and the olives added a good pop of saltiness. Unfortunately my fiancées salad was very disappointing. Only 5 prawns in the whole salad which was too few for the $26 price tag. 85% of the bowl was undressed greens without sufficient dressing to coat them. Pomegranate seeds provided some relief but they were nowhere near as sweet as I would have expected. Service: very quick turnaround of the meals after we ordered despite being packed. We were also allowed to bring in our own cake for my grandmother without being charged extra for cakeage which was a bonus. Value: overpriced for what it was. My pasta was $26 and so was the salad. The salad needed more prawns and not just greens. I personally believe that only the best handmade pasta in a fine dining setting should be over $25. Overall Watergrill is a really nice setting with a beautiful view. However, I feel the price tag of the food does not match the quality.

Pretty location and nice ambience, but we had mixed experiences with the food: Arancini and bread rolls to start were quite nice, but the steak came very well done instead of medium rare (the replacement after we sent it back was *ok*, but not great), and the tahini yoghurt paired with the salmon was a very questionable pairing — if you come here, maybe just grab a nice window seat and stick to the drinks.

The location is superb. Beautiful views of the water and incredible sunsets. Unfortunately it is the overpriced tastless food that lets the venue down. I am a local and a member and have been a few times hoping the food has improved but disappointed each time. Skip the food and go for drinks and the ambience. SRC if you are reading this PLEASE improve the food quality at the Watergrill.

An extremely busy place but gorgeous panoramic views of the water. Easily accessible via rivercat or drive with plenty of parking. Food is great, with healthy gf options also. My favourite is the Rosè flight (vino) a must buy & Frosè if your a wine lover. For $15 you cant beat it! I highly recommend ordering the Barramundi. Delicious! Best to seat outside and enjoy the view. Come early or get no seats!
I loved this place. Beautiful views, a nice little band playing and great food. I want to come back here again so I can watch an amazing sunset while eating and having a couple of drinks 🍸

Very expensive for pub food! I guess you are paying for the ambience and beautiful location - best to come during daylight hours so you can admire the view. We ordered the seafood platter to share which was nice but very expensive, and some of the seafood was overcooked like the lobster. The food was nice and what I expected really, it is just quite expensive for what it is I think
Pretty views with alright food and yummy cocktails! Food is pretty standard pub food but a little bit fancier! Great for family dinner catch ups with a chill vibe 😘

I had a wonderful meal for lunch on Sunday the 11th, it was the atlantic salmon. I don't actually like the idea of food being mounded on top of other food and thats wot they did with the atlantic salmon, I rather the salmon was on the plate just by its self and all the other food around it like they do at Bankstown sports club.

Not great. Not good value for money. Undercooked sauce on kids penne. Needed at least another 30min on the stove to cook out the tomato rawness. Seafood plate didn't have enough on it for the price. 2 ppl on my table ordered this. The coconut type prawns on the platter tasted off and were inedible. Worst dish would have been the pork. Over marinated to the point it was smack in your face. Crap over cooked veggies on the bottom, just not nice at all. Couldn't tell if it was pork or alligator I was eating, couldn't taste it at all cause of marinade. Prawn salad had half an avocado that was rock solid. They forgot dressing so had to go back with it. I will acknowledge that the prawns in the salad were fresh and enjoyable. The place was extremely busy because of location but there are cowboys in the kitchen who just pump out the food with no love. Lots of other good clubs in the area to try.

A kiosk located in the middle of a dog-friendly Sydney park. Today was a beautiful day in Sydney and my family came for a walk early this morning. On the end of our walk we reached a kiosk offering a range of cafe style foods and drinks. I ordered a bacon and egg roll whilst my mum ordered a wrap (forgot what it was called). Average prices for a regular café but relatively quick service and plenty of seating available. Food was delicious and would definitely come here again when I visit Sydney park!
OMG. Amazing catering for kids Birthday Party. Food and service exceptional. Thanks so much Jemma and crew. The parents and children very happy. Highly recommended.

This might be the creamiest coffee I’ve ever had but it was at the expense of any coffee flavour. They were doing a roaring trade on a Sunday but, given that almost all customers were families, I suspect that the food would similarly be “family quality”.

Ordered a humans wrap, just after ordering heard a lady saying it was a bit spicy, so I asked him if it was spicy, he said it wasn't spicy at all. I sat down to eat and the first thing I bit into was a piece of jalapeno chili. I picked out a total of 9 pieces of chill in the wrap. Wrap was expensive and skinny, there's not much else at the park which is why they're still in business, I highly recommend you to bring takeaway or pack a picnic instead.

I ordered a Rueben toasted sandwich which was supposed to have coleslaw at a whopping $9.50. All I got was a couple of pieces of tip top bread, a slice or two of corned beef, a few pieces of peppers and thanks for coming! When I went back to ask where's the coleslaw I got a whole lot of babbling and excuses - NO APOLOGY! What really pissed me off was the arrogant comment one of them made when I asked how they can charge for something and not actually provide it- "we'll do you see any other cafes around here?"😡 what a wanker. If they had just said upfront when I ordered "sorry we're out of coleslaw today" that would have been fine. Instead I got "well we put some sauerkraut on instead. too bad if I hated sauerkraut! Stay away. Coffee isn't great either. NEVER going back and will tell all my friends to boycott. Just a word of advice for you boys - the customer is always right and word of mouth and social media can go a long way in damaging a business' reputation.

Went at a not particularly busy time, but they still couldn't successfully fill a simple coffee order, even with 3 people behind the counter. They weren't really rude, just dopey. Eventual coffee not bad.

This place is so overpriced because of the "captive audience" factor. Not only that but today while I was there the barista/cashier (male, 30's, longish hair, shit attitude) was so rude to a little old lady whose only crime was telling him the freezer wasn't cold enough and that her ice cream was melted. He pretty much yelled at her and she was quite upset. This guy is trash, way to scream at a little old lady with a melted ice cream.
Sydney Park Kiosk is located just next to the amazing playground in Sydney Park. The coffee is excellent and the food is gourmet kiosk fare. Enjoy a great day out with the family.

UPDATE: Nov 2015 and this place is still rude - only this time they were rude to both my wife and a trainee at the kiosk plus the price of the same muffin had gone up $1 in a week. AVOID this place at all costs is my advice. Rude and inattentive service, over priced food prepared with no care. Bring your own food when you come to Sydney Park!

Much Improved!. Wow has this place improved. The food is still quite good but it's the service that is the key. it was previously rude and indifferent, now it is friendly and helpful. The new guy behind the counter as fabulous people skills and boy does it make a difference. If you have felt let down by this place in the past, I would recommend giving it another go. I did and was very happy with the result. I'm a regular again!
Love the burgers here. The meats are so soft and have so much flavour. Love the side of pickles, couples so nicely with the burgers. Can't wait to come back!

Came here with high expectations and was a little disappointed. The staff were friendly. Simple things are neglected IE. food served directly on the trays and no plates provided (meat platter), as well as the cleanliness of the cups provided for the table water. The burgers were decent, but was a bit disappointed with the meat platter, after all. this is supposed to the their speciality. The pork belly wasn’t crispy and the beef short rib was a bit dry.

As promise, {uid:78740554} and his parents took me there, that’s really sweet of them! They waited for me to 2pm and we actually started our lunch at 3pm. Is that “Lunnet” Their ribs were really yummy 😋 crispy outside and tender insides. But some parts were extreme dry and chewy, taste like paper. It’s selling point might be the freshness and convenience as the own a butcher store just next door and the food must from there. Salads were general okay and the chips 🍟 taste like frozen microwave chips — even reheated frozen chips taste better than their chips. Two years ago, in winter I tried their beef burger after I went grocery shopping next door. The memory was vague but at least it’s not too bad to avoid me to visit their store again.

Meat platter is our family usual. It says 2 ppl but i think it can easily feed 3 of us. We still add some extra though just because their food is so nice. The meats are smoked to perfection, melts in your mouth and flavorful even on its own. 3 sauces are offered with the platter. Good value too for smoke house. Also nice to do some meat shopping in their adjacent butcher shop. {uid:43981877} missed out this time but I will take her there next time! Staff is friendly and fast. This is hands down the best smoke house restaurant around! Update: Took Xi here this time and it was hmmm ok

First had to decipher the ordering system. There’s an “order here” sign where the guys prepare the meat but a note on the menu about ordering at the till. I go to the till and I’m sent back to the guys, then I order a brisket sandwich and I’m sent back to the till, where they had a bunch of pre-prepared sandwiches sitting around. The brisket was pretty tender, maybe slightly stringy, but they didn’t seem to have cooked any flavourings into it, so it was bland even by Sydney standards. The sandwich came together well for a decent price though, even had some bits of haloumi in it, and the outlook over the bay is good, just nothing memorable about Vic’s.

Ambience: Just a casual place with a couple of tables. Nothing too special but may get crowded during busy hours. Service: You order at the counter and pick up the food yourself so pree standard service as well. Food: This is the reason you want to come. Great smokey flavour in every cut of meat. Everything is cooked low and slow so it falls off the bone🏻 Recommendations: The beef short rib and the beef brisket.

I sorely miss the Texas smoked beef brisket I had the chance to experience during my travels to the USA, so I was very, very excited to come across Vic's Meat Market at the Sydney Fish Market in Pyrmont. I managed to get some of the "burnt bits" (I think that's what they're called) a couple of times, but missed out on others, because I'm told they go pretty quick. They're essentially the off-cuts so they're cheap though nonetheless delicious. I love visiting the fish market but I can get fresh seafood elsewhere; I can't say the same about smoked beef brisket, so that's ironically the main drawcard for me lately to make the 40-minute drive there.

Perhaps I ordered the most mediocre item from the menu but I felt Vic's Meat Market was a bit overrated. Burger was very average and was more or less the same story with the fries. Really not much to say otherwise, perhaps try something else on the menu though.
Pulled pork burgers & ribs all way! This joint smashes out the most tender and juciest meat! Best to go on a weekday when there are no crowds. Faster service, no line up and you get a seat!

The quick and dirty: great meat, at a lower than average price. What else? - Simple menu- mostly steak, burgers, etc. - if you’re picky and are looking for a variety of cuts, check the menu first, - great to come as a group to sample more food, - open for dinner!

The Pho was surprising good. The joint definitely has a “fast food” feel so you would expect lower quality however the Pho and the range of rice paper roles were actually on point. Wish they didn’t have plastic cutlery but besides that a must visit for lunch.
Quite authentic Vietnamese cuisine. Have many options to choose from, pork roll, pho noodle soup to salad bowl. Definitely a must try when you're in cbd.
Feel good juice that made me feels good! Watermelon, mango, pineapple, were on the mixed. It was thirst quencher during hot day.
The zatar and cheese manoush was quite nice. Great value when you are hungry in the morning. Line was quite long sometime, but moved quite fast.

user.profile_name: Hungry Teddy (20% Zomato Gold, Use : HUNG2716)

review.text: Pablo and Rusty’s powering this coffee shop. This shop has been around since I remembered and just did the renovations. I don’t mind the taste, first coffee since I landed in land of OZ today.

Best Manoush in Sydney. The meat and cheese is my favourite. I come here EVERY time I go to the airport. You can still get here even if you are departing, by going down the escalators after you have dropped off your baggage.  Unfortunately the location is hugely inconvenient unless you are going to the airport, and they don't have any other branches (I checked with them). Friendly staff, great food.

Amazing little food pockets and the staffs were so friendly! Bonus: it's cheap as well! They run the items through the oven just before serving so it's hot and crispy. The dough isn't too thick and the filling was very well spiced. Would definitely prefer to go here over the generic fast food chains. Glad to see a local business greeting our guests.
New pop-up at the airport that's well worth a visit. Located just outside the arrivals terminal, there's a great selection of Lebanese breads, which is perfect when served warm.

Got an iced latte today and I kid you not, half my cup was ice. At $4.50, pretty expensive for some frozen water. A “tall” cup wasn’t that big either. Makes bubble tea look like good value in comparison.

Friendly and fast service. The seating areas always seem full. Coffee is always good. It may not be boutique, flavoursome coffee, but I can be confident knowing each time I order I will get a decent coffee. The staff always make time to have a chat and smile.

After a lacklustre lunch at Jackpot Dining we had enough time for a quick cuppa at Zarraffa's in Toowong Village. The large double shot Cappuccino ($5.10) went down well. The coffee was good, not great but still better than Jamaica Blue around the corner. Thanks guys!
Their cappuccino was ok. Not so special but it was good enough and price is reasonable. They have some place to sit in which is good. The service not so fast tho.

I have a special place for Zarraffa's coffee in my heart. This is the place I had my first coffee in Australia. I am an ardent coffee fan and have tasted coffee at umpteen number of places. Zarraffa's is good. I will not say it's the best but it's good. Some of my favs are White chocolate mocha, Caramelized fusion, Caramelized cappuccino. Conveniently located right in the middle of the Toowong shopping complex with friendly staff. I have visited this place many times and will keep visiting.

All I can say is, Starbucks>Gloria Jeans>Zaraffas. Nothing impresses me about Zaraffas anymore. This wasn't always the case but it would be silly to say that Zaraffas is still on par with their competitors currently! Disappointed, to say the least!

Great coffee, a bit expensive but the flavors are perfecto ! Charging for extra shots ( u just get one shot regardless of the size you order ) in larger sizes after you have paid for a bigger size is just double dipping on the price. Anyhoo I still like the coffee !

Beautiful Staff. I get my regular americano right on 7 30 as the store opens and its always crisp fresh and helps me get off to a good start! thank you zarraffas staff, your papa newguinean beans are also soo lovely too when i cant make it in store.

Visiting Morayfield recently noticed a Zarraffas outlet. As I have one of their cards decided to use it & chose a small flat white with two shots. As usual it didn't come to the par on strength but flavor was good hence scoring of 3

Got a caramelized mocha lady behind counter stuffed up the order so gave us a largfe instead of a regular, it was full of sugar ( disgusting)  my kidney hurt for 4hrs after not good. I usually like zarrafas coffee though. Wont be trying that next time

Staff. The friendly staff lead by Tina, Leisha and Carmel at Zarraffas Morayfield make the coffee experience remarkable. I recommend to any one going past Morayfield Shopping Centre to drop in and say hello. They will treat you not only with great coffee and a smile but if you look as though you have had a bad day they will cheer you up. The best Zarraffas franchise in Brisbane!

Never had a better mocha!. Seriously. I've had coffee all over the world, and I always look forward to getting back to Morayfield and having a Zarraffa's mocha. I think it's the fact that they actually use their own chocolate fudge recipe to make mochas that gives theirs its distinctive taste; it is a culinary treat! All of their coffee is of a superb quality, and any coffee aficionado is well advised to stop and have a drink at this café.
Excellent!. Great hot chocolates, cakes and coffee!.
The staff are the most fabulous people! I love them. could mean I drink too much coffee that they remember me. food is good for the price you pay. Mocha is awesome.

Phuong Tran and I decide on a meaty Saturday dinner so Korean BBQ Buffet it is! Midam is a comfortable and well ventilated restaurant and on arrival we are politely greeted and seated. The Buffet is $37.90 pp and includes some cooked food, a selection of raw meats, salads, side dishes, sliced oranges and cold water. It is a full house with most tables ordering the Korean BBQ. I expected a variety of sliced fruits, ice cream, soft drinks/juices for the price. And both times when I asked staff for more prawns, the tray returned with 10-12 tiny prawns for 60 patrons.😂 Overall, we had a decent meal but I am not sure we will return for the BBQ Buffet.

A very clean, well decorated restaurant with wonderful service and fantastic food. Average pricing but the cuts of meat are well worth the money. Far and away my favourite Korean BBQ south of the city.
Very over priced and small proportion. Had to wait 40 mins to get our food

My Korean friend highly recommends the 'Midam' which is a restaurant that has both a Korean BBQ buffet and a lot of meals. My favourite one is superb sweet chilli fried chicken, come with a side of salad. It's such a perfect spot for Korean lover.
Delicious authentic Korean food. Tried both the bbq buffet and their ala carte menu. Very nice. Definitely would go more often with my wife, she loves the Korean bbq. Especially the ox tongue

Was invite out by my brother for a catch up dinner and he felt like Korean bbq. With so many booked out and needing a table of 10, Midam was the only one to offer 2 tables side by side. We arrive and greeted by friendly staff and shown to our tables with my brother already there. So we went with the buffet, @$37.50 a head. Also added 3 extra dishes. Then the fun began, everyone went to get their dishes to start cooking, among sides and fried foods like spring rolls, fried chicken, fish balls, glass noodles, pasta salad. After a little wait, they bring out the hot coal for bbq cooking. We had ox tounge, pork belly, steak, chicken and plenty of others too. All self service, they also change the hot plate when dirty. Food was good, we all enjoyed our meal are way too much. Only down side is the smell of bbq after, also a bottle of iced tea for $6.50 and a bottle of beer only $6 something isn't right. There is only so much you can eat at all you can eat.

This place is just fabulous. Took my best friends here and we all had the buffet and it was absolutely worth every cent. The meats were fresh and delicious, the sides were abundant, the kimchi was excellent and the drinks specials were good too. If you go here, remember to take your biggest appetite.  Midam also has a great setup and decor and I think I spotted little private rooms you can book to get you away from the general eating area.

We decided to dine here Friday night. Our little group of four love Korean BBQ so between the four of us we shared a Premium Wagyu Beef Set A and Mini Pork Set D. We all rolled out of Midam very full and very satisfied

Arrived on a Sunday evening and was promptly seated. They have buffet style Korean bbq for ~$38 pp and also the a-la-carte menu. We weren’t too hungry so opted for the menu option (although we were stuffed at the end). We ordered a beef rib hot pot, bibimbap, mini beef set, and kimchi noodles. Food came promptly and with banchan. The portions were generous and the meat was fairly fresh. When you order bbq sets you can order diff side dishes for a fraction of the full price. Overall, it was a great variety and food was pretty good. Will definitely be back to try the Korean bbq buffet when craving a huge meat feed.

We meant to re-visit the Sichuan Spice restaurant but it was fully booked for private function so went next door to explore this Korean eatery. Not because that, we probably keep continuously missing the improvement of this restaurant.  We were greeted by the friendly wait-staff when we walked in and one of them led us to the area to have a la cart after we indicated our purpose of dine-in. Then we were showed the offer of early bird specials on a menu so we might as well to follow their promotion to have a hot stone braised beef short rib and a hot stone seafood soup with additional order of an entrée of pan-fried dumplings. Honestly, dumplings are only passable but the other two dishes are too outstanding.  The beef ribs are slow-cooked to perfection that fall apart from the bone. Turnip pieces absorb all the flavour and they are soft. Glass noodles are extra-surprise. Besides that the seafood soup is made of many seafood with shelled prawns, mussels, half sand crab and squid. If not because the disgusting fly keep attacking us and the ventilation is not good inside the restaurant, full mark will be granted for this review.  Rating 4.5/5    Jun 26, 2015  Rating 3/5  Located next to Sichuan Spice Chinese restaurant at Farne Street. I found this restaurant is always busy with Korean diners. Tried it one night but I could not find any significant competitive power of this restaurant against its competitors; again, a la carte with option of buffet "all-you-can-eat". Although they provide a huge spacious dining area, large range of meat varieties for buffet and also charcoal grill, I just found that there are overwhelming supplies of this type of trading strategy. Are there any different dishes in the menu? Think about it!

Great lunch and breakfast food made fresh daily. I occasionally stop by here for a quick lunch or breakfast fix. Baguettes are to die for, they use authentic french baguettes which I don't think you could get anywhere else in the CBD. Coffee is also great.

I had been to this cafe many years ago & reviewed it, my review has disappeared so am assuming they have had an ownership change? I remember my original opinion of the coffee here was unfavorable, but this time I was presented with a great cup of Toby's Estate. Double shot was standard in a small cup resulting in a rich smooth brew

I went to Cool Beans and Baguettes for a quick lunch. I chose a pre-made salad and a small fresh juice. I chose the super power salad because the ingredients listed on the top looked healthy and included all things I like. I asked for my favourite juice combo. I was surprised that this came to $15 - it seemed just a few dollars too much but I figured that was the cost of a CBD meal. After I sat down I was informed there was no beetroot for my favourite juice. I substituted with orange. I was slightly disappointed until it arrived and it was delicious. The salad included raw eschallots which were not listed on the ingredients and have an unexpected raw onion flavour- another disappointment. Overall, my lunch was okay. The service was friendly and the good was ready to go but just a couple of niggles that would stop me rushing back.
Fresh not fried! Refreshing healthier version to quick lunch options at the top end of town including some yummy salads, no carb options, gluten free, yoghurts & snacks.
Saturday morning just around the corner coffee aid. love the coffee here, but it just took a little too long for the wait. saw some breakfast made. it was huge ! gotta try it sometime.
Love this place! Quite surprised to see the negativity about it on here. Amazing coffees, service and excellent location. What more could you ask for?

The barista at cool beans is fast and the coffee is amazing. A real shame about a couple of really unhelpful and rude counter staff. Won't be going back there or recommending this place to my business.

You don't know what you're talking about !. To Braddos87 you wouldn't now a great coffee it leaped up and hit you in the face ! and having to have a 'bad' one before you go the gym, maybe give the gym up that way you won't be 'forced to drink 'bad' coffee. Everyone in the area misses this shop for it's great coffee and friendly and fast service and reasonable pricing. No matter how busy Gus was, he could pump coffees out of there at a rapid and consistent pace. So sad they were forced to close. Damn hard to find a decent, reasonably priced coffee around Brisbane Square now.

Consistently bad coffee. This place no longer exists, but have been meaning to write this review for a while because of how consistently bad the coffee is. oddly, people I work with frequent this place, I do not know why. 2 colleagues and I (who love great coffee) frequently criticise just how awful the coffee here was and we are confused as to why our other colleagues praise this place. good to see other reviewers share the same opinion. out of a caffeine necessity, I need to get an espresso hit before gym to wake me up. without fail, the coffee has always been burnt. it tastes absolutely disgusting, but does it job of waking me up for gym nonetheless. so glad this place is no longer open. i can only hope a much better coffee provider/barista takes its place in refurbishments.

We go to cool beans and baguettes twice a week for coffee before work. The service is always friendly and the coffee is always nice. Two extra special things I like about cool beans, the fantale they give with each coffee, and the very generous buy 5, get 1 free coffee cards.
Got a quick takeaway of mee goreng tonight. Pretty good and the ingredients are fresh. The setup is a bit simplistic but at least the food was good. Will be back again
Excellent fresh Asian food. At last a decent local take away. Don't be put off by the no frills shop. The food is great and excellent value. Keep up the good work.

Hard to find good hearty Chinese food around Brisbane I feel, but Asian Food Paradise is our go to shop when we want Chinese. I live up the road from them and when I Order over the phone they say it'll be ready in 15 minutes, 15 minutes later drive down to get it BANG. it's ready. Very friendly service, prices are affordable, tasty food & quick service.

Asian Food Paradise - Holland Park, Brisbane. Located in simultaneously an awkward yet proximal place, Asian Food Paradise is snuggled in an array of stores on a side street just off multiple main roads (and across the lane from a gas station, to boot). As standard looking as it may be (it is nothing that is unique), if approached with an open mind it is quite a wholesome choice. It is more a take-out than anything; there is the presence of tables for people waiting for their order. The waitress there did what she need to do, and was helpful in my order (I paid by EFTPOS, but was under the minimum - a half order of an entree was allowed). When the order was placed, she suggested to sit down - quite courteous. There was not a lot to the interior, it was a small area for takeaway. It did embelish family-orientation. For my order, there was a $7 lunch special menu (with $1 extra for fried rice and $1 for a can of soda with the exception of Coke) of 15 or so dishes. I chose a salt and pepper chicken with fried rice and a half order of spring rolls. The dish was surprisingly spicy, an agreeable temperature and translated pretty well. There could be improvement on the fried rice - it was a bit plain for fried rice and could have had more substance (such as egg, corn etc) and would have suffered if it was eaten by itself. The spring rolls were better than average and I could detect actual ingredients in the filling. Overall, a decent meal for the folk short on time. I have been to Asian Food Paradise several times before, and they have had good food - slightly different from the Chinese and Thai that are common in the situated area. This time, Asian Food Paradise did not disappoint and I will certainly consider returning.

For any newly integrated residents, this would be a good place because of its value; it would also be good for any families of young children and university students (who remembers those days?). Nothing about it really stands out from the inside, but it is a very wholesome place.

Visited Carindale Grill’d multiple times this month, thanks to the good-cause collaboration with Polished Man. Every visit delivered fantastic food and great service by staff. Food always came out in a timely manner, no matter what time of day it was.

Had an amazing birthday dinner here. I called up to reserve a place and they fitted me in, then gave me a free meal for my birthday, which I didn't realise they did. As we were getting ready to leave they bring out a fredo ice cream cake with sparklers for me. It was wonderful and I really enjoyed the night. The burgers were amazing as usual, and my vegans friends even enjoyed their burgers.

This Grill’d gets very busy, and has limited seating. However the service has always been good and I cannot complain about anything that has come from the assembly line. Not worth traveling for the ambience - but ok if they are not too busy and you feel like a predictable tasty burger

I really love the burgers here Staff are always friendly and they ensured my daughter had colouring pencils and paper for colouring in while she waited for her lunch My go to meal before a movie then I don’t have to load up on overpriced snacks at the cinema lol
Very nice burgers but I wish they were better value for money. Can be difficult finding seating during busy times. Service is good and food comes out fast.

Great! Burgers are a flavour bomb of juicy beef crunchy veg and umami happiness. Fries are mouth watering but too salted at times. Service can be slow but employees are very aware and get right on it. 3 minute checks are very professional.

Pretty good menu but pricey. Not a place to have a relaxing lunch. It is busy and can therefore be noisy. Felt very unwelcome by the staff. A girl was positioned at the entrance to the store. Great idea if the point is to welcome customers but with her attitude and lack of warmth she actually repelled me so I looked elsewhere. I decided to try again as it felt silly to be put off by a "vibe" - but sure enough my feeling was right. She definately oozed an attitude that she didn't want to be there, mirrored by several other staff there. What I will give them points for was how hard they were working. So a pretty average experience all round for me.

I was looking for a great place to eat, and I stumbled upon Grill'd. I chose a hamburger and it was delicious. The only problem is that the burger kept falling apart. Everything was fine and the service was nice. We also got to donate but the choices of donations were poor. Great place for a great burger.

Love Grilld as a fast , well priced meal for the family. The burgers are always fresh and packed full of yum ingredients. My favourite is the sunset burger and I love that they offer a low carb bun! The burgers are so packed full of great flavours , one burger is all I can fit in and I walk away so full. Great value for healthy, wholesome food😊 they also make donations to local charities which is great 👍

I’ve had many great lunches at Grill'd. On my first visit I ordered the Friends of Falafel on Panini and a small sweet potato fries. Both were delicious. I really couldn't fault it. The service was both very prompt and very friendly. I’ve continued to sample the menu and everything I’ve tasted has been great (apart from the low carb bun). The hemp and pea patty I had last weekend was delicious. It’s great that there are so many vegetarian options. This is about as good as fast food gets.
Go here most weekends, food is always great and a nice place to meet friends for drinks. Dogs allowed in one area too.

Came here on Sunday for lunch with the family to celebrate two birthdays (30th and a 36th) which made it very special. The booking was made for 8 people and confirmed it twice with the staff before arriving. The table that was allocated was not enough to seat 8 adults, I requested the table to be changed and by the time I returned, the table was allocated to someone else although it was reserved for us. I requested the staff for another table, but they directed us to go back and stand in line to talk to reservation staff - which i did.(my family was standing around for about 20 mins until we were served down the line) Then they managed to find another table with high chairs which went not suitable for my older parents/grandparents so we requested a similar table to what we originally had with more room. Then the gentlemen at the pizzeria offered some seating but then other staff eventually asked us to leave as there was a party set up. My family and I had to walk away - we did NOT receive an apology and they did not try to address/rectify the issue. They ruined our birthday plans and very unprofessional approach- they could have spoken to the people who sat on our reserved table but instead kicked us out . We had family from overseas as well so this was a very unpleasant experience. My family and I will make sure that we share our experience with our extended family and friends especially those that are local. We will not return to this establishment again.

Get told to walk to back ofbuilding. Stand in line. Finally get served and order. "What's your table number?" Wtf? I have no table i am ordering breakfast. You need a table number to order. So i wasted 10 minutes in line now i have to find a table and come back. Shove it i go next door. How freaking rude

Went for lunch last weekend, beautiful outlook over the bay too bad I can’t say the same about the food. Ordered steak for lunch and come out very much over cooked with out a decent slaw as it was just a little bit of red cabbage in a tiny bowl. Very disappointing and won’t be back.
Always nice to have a meal at this place! We have been there many times and always happy with our food! Nice view and nice staff. Very big place!

Best thing about The Belvedere is the open deck overlooking the jetty & waterfront & the fact that your pooch is welcome on it too! Which is the main reason for a 3 score. Food is another story, a bit underwhelming, remember it is a pub after all be it renovated or whatever. Rather a long wait for our breakfast & we were pretty early so it wasn't ultra busy. When it did arrive coffee & food came together, coffee was haphazardly spilled in both saucers with no offer of a clean up or replacement. Food was semi warm ( big turn off for me) Luckily it consisted mainly of avocado, the accompanying haloumi was cold & rubbery & looked very sad! Ditto the fried eggs & dry teeth breaking toast. Oh well that view.

Food lacks any balance of flavour and coffee is under extracted and lukewarm. I had a pizza and the sauce was so sparse and the prosciutto was definitely old as it had that slimy moth feel Amazing location but needs work.

Used to be our regular go-to dinner. Have lived locally for 2 years and throughout that time it’s just been going downhill. Staff are super friendly, and it’s a beautiful spot but the food leaves a lot to be desired. Used to be packed with flavour and great value, but now it’s expensive and bland. So much potential in this place, it’s a shame that’s going to waste.

Went for lunch during the week and ordered the burger and nachos. Pretty disappointing and overpriced. The nachos included corn chips, meat and guacamole. No cheese or salsa, very dry and really odd. The burger was ok but pretty cold by the time it got to us. The wait stuff all had conflicting info about what each meal consisted of and I ended up just talking to the people in the kitchen behind the counter about what I needed due to allergies. Pretty disappointing and won’t be back.

The Belvedere is always our go to, as it’s family friendly and the views are fantastic. We even had our daughters christening there last year . After the renovations, the food was amazing and we recommended it to everyone, but over the last few months we have been really disappointed with our food and there seems to be a lack of love going in to the meals. We ordered a kids burger and an adult burger and the portion was exactly the same with an $8 difference, I had a seafood pizza which would have been lovely if it hadn’t been smothered in Marie sauce which ruined it, and really below average calamari from the starter menu with a dry salad and rubbery calamari. We don’t want to stop coming here or say a bad word, but it’s got to the point where I think something needs to changed in the kitchen. Also bring back the Mac and cheese balls and the corn cobs. That was when the menu was top notch!

The disrespect on the staff members on each other that I have witness yesterday, I question how they train staff. I ordered through front counter and was served by a nice lady yesterday evening/night and the whole time I was ordering another chick kept popping up out of nowhere trying to help the lady who was serving me but at the end, she read back all my order correctly. While I was waiting for my order I kept noticing the same chick popping up out of nowhere and that every time she 'tries' to help the front counter lady most orders came out wrong and most customers were furious including myself because somehow my order was completely wrong. and the manager at the time was no help at all! and made it even worse. There could've been ways to solve whatever was going on. like maybe swapping the packer and the till person. or just maybe not be so unprofessional in-front of customers. The behaviour shown between co-workers yesterday is disgusting and it was such eye sore to watch a coworker visibly being nasty to another co-worker. My advice is to do your job correctly and to communicate as a team because I did not see that at all yesterday.
This is NOT North Lakes. De. This is NOT North Lakes. Deception Bay all :-)
My first meal here was 36 years ago and tonight hasn’t disappointed . well done . from entree to dessert the quality has been excellent.

The short soup was amazing. Excellent chinese food. Not very greasy with a great mixture of vegetables. Fried rice, combination chow mein and salt and pepper pork rib were all worth it. Reasonably priced and friendly service.
Food: not the usual authentic Chinese food. It tasted alright but not great though the cashew chicken order was suggested by the waitstaff. Service: not as friendly

I've been here in the past a few times and found reasonably good. This time however was really disappointing. Each dish came out 15 minutes apart with the rice coming out last. So we really couldn't start until half the dishes were cold. Food was average, lacking fresh vegetables. The young fellow started clearing our table, including our placemats and napkins before all of us had finished eating.

VALUE AND TASTE. We have been frequent guests at Willow Garden Restaurant(approx 2-3 times per month) during the past 4 years. My wife is Asian and is always seeking authentic tastes. We have always enjoyed the meals and friendliness of the owner and staff. Even though the restaurant is mostly quiet(how we like it) the take-away section of Willow Garden is consistently busy, maybe explaining some of the waiting time in the restaurant mentioned by another reviewer. They need to realize that, even though there are only a few tables occupied, the kitchen staff are cooking for another 20 tables via take-away. The Chinese art and decor on display is impressive and that hint of the 70's in the bar decor just adds to the atmosphere. In our many visits we've never been disappointed.
Worst Chinese ever.

Waited over an hour for food, staff forgot orders, tried to overcharge- awful!. We went to Willow Garden for a family birthday dinner. There was six of us and only one other occupied table in the restaurant, yet somehow it took over an hour for all our mains to be brought out. By the time my egg noodles came, everyone else had finished their food. The wait staff did not check up on us, so if we wanted to order a drink we had to walk up to the cash register and wait to be attended. The drink never came, so we had to ask again twenty minutes later. We ordered four fried ice creams to follow our meals, but they never came. Everyone else had left the restaurant and we were still there waiting for food as the staff were mopping the floors out the front. By then we'd been there for two hours. We tried to find someone to ask about the progress of the order, but were told it was "coming". It had been about 40 minutes since we finished our meals when we asked for a second time about the order, and the waitress informed us that they had forgotten about it. Argh! When we went to pay, there was an added charge on our bill. It turned out that instead of bringing us the entree for four that we had ordered (two people in our group of 6 were vego), they had brought us an entree for six and thus doubled the price. The woman behind the counter refused to change the amount. We were already aggravated after waiting so long for food and drinks that never came. It ruined the occasion and left us all feeling unfulfilled and annoyed. How can you have such sloppy service when there's only one table you have to look after? Never go to Willow Garden!
We have always been a fan of this Chinese restaurant. Great food and affordable. Always fresh and well cooked. Eating in is also nice.

Excellent service.food well above the best i have had.this restraunt has raised the bar for other asian eateries.the dining room is just right.no noise from the traffic comes into the place.i would give willow gardens a rating of 8.5 out of ten the night we went there.in all the wiow garden made the night great.

Unfortunately very bland food. Just went to Willow Garden for lunch. We were the only people there which concerned me to start with. We had mixed entree, crispy duck with orange sauce, sweet & sour pork with special fried rice, washed down with green tea. All very bland. The duck should have been called cremated duck not crispy duck. It was so dry and as tasteless as the rest of our meal. very disappointed. The seach is still on for quality Chinese in Brisbane suberbs!

Good Malaysian hawker food We visited Dapur Dahlia at their now not so new premises opposite the Buranda shopping centre for lunch on Sunday - which are a huge step up from their old premises at Mount Gravatt. Unfortunately no roti was available so we tried the dry curry mee with chicken, seafood laksa lemak, fried chicken and a taro pudding for dessert. The dry curry mee was very good but we weren't that impressed with the laksa - it had a more buttery rather than coconut milk flavour and they used short fat rice noodles ("mouse tail" noodles) which are not our favourite. The food here is Malay style rather than Chinese Malaysian style so I don't think that this is the place to eat noodles. We're going to come back and try the nasi lemak (which looked amazing) and some roti! They have a good coffee machine and use Wolff Coffee which was excellent.

There are many Malaysian Chinese restaurants around Brisbane. My 600th food review is on this Malaysian Malay restaurant. I feel welcome as I walk up to the counter. The smiling Manager is happy to explain the menu to me as I place my order and pay at the counter. *Chicken Satay ($12) has four Chicken Skewers served with a Satay Peanut Sauce and several slices of raw onion and cucumber. Ketupat (compressed rice) is available for $2. These Chicken Skewers are grilled under an electric stove as charcoal grilling is banned. The Chicken is nicely marinated, tasty and tender. Dipped in the Satay Sauce, this is a delicious entree. Highly recommended! Many restaurants deep fry their Satay Skewers to save time. This is blasphemy and an unheard of practice in Malaysia. Rating: 4.5 *Nasi Lemak with Beef Rendang ($13) comes with steamed rice, half boiled egg, Sambal, Peanuts and Fried Anchovies. I was disappointed coconut rice was not served. The Beef Rendang and Sambal is delicious but the overall serving is small compared to Papparich, Taste of Penang, Sri Makhota, Malaya Corner and Singapore & Co. Rating: 4 * Kuih Lapis (3 for $5) is left uncovered in the refrigerated cabinet. Hence, the top layer is hard and inedible while the rest of the Kuih tastes quite average. Not recommended. Rating: 3 This restaurant has an interesting Malay Menu. I will return with my family to try some traditional Malay dishes. Thank you guys!

Have not been back since my first review nearly 5 years ago. They might have changed the location because I found the venue is different from last time but more spacious and modernised.  Incidentally, I was back from Penang prior to the exploration so found that the way that they prepared the Malaysian dishes was different from what I had in Malaysia. Having said that it does not mean that they are not authentic. Portions were still not generous as before but very tasteful; particularly the satay sauce. We has the dinner at mid-March with voucher deal, otherwise we might paid over-prices there.   Rating 3.5/5      Aug 09, 2014  Rating 3/5  Authentic or valuable?. Have tried the Satay Ayam, Ayam Goreng, Seafood Laksa and Seafood Mee Goreng. Feeling is so so.   One thing that wouldn't score the 'like' is the small portion that they served. Being a Malaysian restaurant, it is definitely fair to provide authentic Malaysian food, however, customers always would like to have larger portion for value and appetite particular when the food is yummy.   Char-grilled Chicken satay just done perfect with nice sweet satay sauce, however, the Ayam Goreng (Fried chicken wing) was dry and tasteless. Mee Goreng only comes with two small pieces of prawn and some half-cut fish balls and the noodle was too hard (seems under-cooked). The seafood Laksa was done with different types of noodles than other Malyasian restaurants, which may due to the fact that the chef is originated from different part of Malaysia but the Laksa did not give me the usual taste, not to mention the one that I had in Malaysia at KL & Ipoh. General impression, I prefer Little Singapore or Satay Ria.

Malaysian food is known for its diversity as we are a multicultural country and Dapur Dahlia specialises more in Malay style Malaysian food rather than the chinese version. I was excited because I get to try some chicken satay; I usually avoid ordering satay because they could not beat those from home. But I gave Dapur Dahlia a chance and they certainly did not disappoint. The satay sticks were grilled rather than just coated with peanut sauce. It was fairly close to the ones from back home. Their peanut sauce was rather authentic and well-balanced.

I have been a supporter of Dapur Dahlia when they were at Upper Mt Gravatt, and finally had the chance to visit after they relocated. The ambience was nice and welcoming. My fiance ordered nasi lemak with beef rendang, while I ordered their special of the day which was beef, chicken and fish ball soup with noodles. We also ordered teh tarik and sardine karipap. There were 2 other tables occupied whom hadn't got their food, so understandably there was quite a wait for ours. Our sardine karipap came first, followed by my fiance's nasi lemak shortly after. I watched on as one by one the dishes for the other tables came out. Eventually everyone in the restaurant was eating, apart from me. At this point, my fiance had already finished 3 quarters of his meal. I asked the waitress about my soup and she said that the kitchen had forgotten about my order as there were only 2 cooks in the kitchen (not sure how this poses a challenge). I do not understand what was so difficult about putting together a bowl of soup (the stock/broth should already been boiling away in a pot), just had to throw in the noodles and meatballs! When the soup finally came, I had lost my appetite as I was very unhappy. The vermicelli noodles looked sad, there were only 6 tiny meatballs. The soup was overpowering with white pepper. It was obviously put together in a rush without any attention to detail. If we hadn't paid beforehand I seriously considered walking out. I voiced my dissatisfaction, the waitress apologised and offered 2 slices of kuih seri muka as compensation. At least there was some customer service provided. If the restaurant was jam packed and service was busy, I can understand that it would be easy to forget an order; but this was on a rainy Sunday, with only 3 tables to serve. What was the most frustrating part? That the manager(?) was sitting not far from us typing away on his laptop, and he did not try to rectify the situation. Very disappointed.
Was a bad experience with the milo having tap water and costing $7 staff looked lost and confused when asking about different meals ended up needing to buy takeaway for all as no one felt fed enough.

I assume they’be already changed their menu since what I bought was different to what it looks like in zomato menu. Staffs are very friendly and knowledgable. They kindly explained what they currently had for lunch special. I went for nasi campur set with seafood (15$). The special menu was stir fried squid.
