Although the seasoning was bland, I was quite satisfied with how well they cook the squid. It came in a nice texture. Still chewy yet not hard. Their special lunch comes with a free drink. I got an iced coffee which was just fine.

DD has recently moved to Woollongabba on Ipswich Rd. They're not located in Ipswich! The new shop comes with new staff and much more consistent quality in food. We tried our favorites, Nasi lemak with beef rendang, Nasi goreng with ayam goreng and roti canai. They were slightly different to what we were getting at the old shop. Of course this doesn't mean it was worse. We visited mid week for lunch so will return one evening on a weekend to compare. Overall I was pleased with everything. Loved the teh Tarik and teh halia.

I love Malaysian food so its a wonder that I hadn't already been to Dapur Dahlia in my travels! I decided that VGirl and her boyfriend, Zbag, JGirl, Dr S., and myself, should all head here for dinner one day. Dapur Dahlia is a bit hard to spot, its pretty near to the Pizza Hut/Night Owl store in Upper Mount Gravatt so keep an eye out for that. Parking is a bit limited since its not particularly a big shopping lot. This restaurant is super popular, while the Indian restaurant beside it had barely any customers the entire time we were there. Perhaps they should expand that way?

Decided to give it a try due to those positive reviews (they were old ones though). The first look at the shop from the parking made us hesitate whether we should step in or go somewhere else. The place looked very tiny, cheap and unwelcoming. There was only a table of 4 people and a couple of people waiting for their takeaway. We seated ourselves inside and instantly a guy (wearing very casual) brought us menus. He was very friendly and talkative. He started very well with introducing specials of the night; unfortunately, he couldn't explain what they actually were. I googled some images by using the names of those food, and ordered one of the specials. The special was disappointing- all deep fried stuff that tasted like kept overnight in the fridge and over reheated and served with peanut sauce that overwhelmed with sweetness. Our second dish was Roti Jala which was crepes served with chicken curry. The crepes were quite interesting, but the curry was cold and as shown in the photo there were only few pieces of chicken. For mains, I had Laksa with seafood. Hmmm it was quite flavoursome though the soup was way too rich. My partner had Makki Goreng with chicken, and he was quite happy with it.
The food was delicious and such friendly staff, our family will become regulars here. Great pricing for the serving you get, both dine in and take away!

My husband and I ordered takeaway from this restaurant only to get rotten prawns in the pad Thai we had ordered and the roti bread was so oily like it had been sitting there for weeks and been reheated. Unfortunately I ate a prawn before smelling them or realising they were off. My husband took the meals back the day following as we requested a refund due to not eating any of it when taking the meals back my husband stood on a huge cockroach in the restaurant. The worst experience we have ever had with food. Avoid this place at all costs!

We got take away. We shared it as an extended family of about 10 people. We ordered the satay chicken sticks. Larb mince chicken. Red curry chicken. Beef and oyster. Chicken and cashew nut. Fried rice with pineapple. Thai noodles. Everyone loved it even the teenagers who are not normally adventurous in their eating tried and got a pleasant surprise. We even got a free bonus entree. I would go there again if I didn’t live so far away

Worst Thai I have ever had.  Taste was ok and all good - however portions were watered down.  WTH is with loading a "seafood curry" with more pieces of tofu than seafood?  If we wanted (or ate) tofu - we would have asked for it.  Not a mussel in sight - which was another first.  Just 3 prawns and 4 pieces of calamari - and 80% curry water.  The coconut rice is not normal that one gets everywhere else - and was below average - dry - and even with the excessive curry water to soak it up, was still too dry.  Chicken curry was ok - and thank goodness lacked any tofu - with acceptable portions of meat. At $90 - will be going to a lot of better options in Rothwell & North Lakes.
Hands down best Thai I’ve had. Very fresh, well priced and great portions. Vegetable spring rolls on point 🏼 Will become a regular haunt.

lovely food and friendly staff. crispy pork prik khing is delicious but needs more chilli kick. Half point deduction only because take away lid wasn't placed on tightly and most of sauce ended up in the carry bag which meant a very dry curry for dinner. Spring Rolls were probably the best I've had in a long while. Will continue to buy from here.
My local Thai - tasty, fresh and includes more vegetables than elsewhere. Can always rely on the duck pad Thai and curry to hit the spot. Super quick from order to pick-up.

Had some lovely, tasty food, Tom yum soup, chicken green curry and coconut rice, the soup was very flavoursome, with a nice kick to it, the curry was tasty and the coconut rice complemented nicely with it. The staff were friendly and the food was packed well. Would recommend and will be back .

Good, reliable local restaurant. Favourites are the Pad Thai and Garlic & Pepper Chicken (done with ground black peppercorns, which is a little spicier than I'm accustomed to elsewhere). Friendly, quick service.
Now 'Thai Sa-On' has 2 shops at "Burpengary",Phone : +617 3888 7116  and at "RedCliffe" ,Phone :+617 3284 0744 , let's try with the new good management team.

review.text: I always order on menulog beforehand so I get a good look at the menu. And then the order is ready by the time I’m there to pick up. I’ve ordered maybe 4 times from Sushi Shou. They have yet to get an order wrong. It’s not the best sushi I’ve ever had but it’s delicious, cost effective and convenient (only 5 minutes from home). My favourites are the cooked tuna and avo; and fresh salmon and avo. The curry is also nice.
Best Sushi in Brisbane - so fresh and delicious. The assorted sushi platter is good value

My past two meals here with Sushi 79 have been mediocre, with both meals rating 3! Well, Sushi 79 is now Sushi Shou and they must have a new Chef. My light meal here was surprisingly good. The Karaage Chicken was nicely presented, tender and delicious with their mayo dressing. The Okonomiyaki was as good as I have tasted anywhere in Brisbane. And the Miso Soup was hot and tasty. Both meals were served on proper crockery, no longer takeaway boxes. Well done guys!

I will never eat here again. I ordered a teriyaki bento box, veggie option. The other options included chicken, beef and fish. As someone who hasnt eaten meat or fish for over a decade, I chose the veggie option. It arrived with 1 prawn and 2 salmon sushi rolls. I rang the store and the owner told me I didnt understand what I was ordering. He was obnoxious and I (understandably) got very angry I laid a complaint with uber eats and they refunded me within 10 minutes, as they got it If you offer a veggie option, as well as a separate fish option, then you can't serve fish in the veggie option. I will never eat here again.
Taking order that can completed now have to wait for my money for 10 or more days never again this place and Uber Eats bad combination.So disappointed.
Get a platter. It's great quality fish, fantastic for a post workout meal. They're very generous on the avocado and you'll get you money's worth
Absolutely love this sushi shop. Food is always freshly made to order and delicious. The chef specialties are also a very nice alternative to shake things up.
This is my favourite sushi place in Brisbane. Top quality sushi every time I've been, made fresh to order, decent sized portions, would highly recommend if you are in the Jindalee area

One of my favourite Sushi places! I call in quite often as i am in the area a lot. or maybe i am in the area a lot so that i have a reason to call in?! haha I absolutely love the tuna rolls with avo, and in my opinion they are up there with the best in Brisbane! I get the gyoza too when I'm feeling a little more glutenous!  Very modest little shop, tucked away in Jindalee! Must try!

I have stopped buying sushi from here and the last few times it has been yuck. My tuna wasn't nice and the avocado wasn't ripe. My partner hasn't enjoyed his sushi the last few times either. It used to be really good but has gone downhill. The one in bellbowrie is really good though.
It was disgusting food mould on the bread roll chips were dry and cold. It was gross asked why bread was mouldy they said that’s the way the bread is.
If there is a no star rating, I’d give it a zero star. Horrible fish and chips, both soggy and cold, the best was probably the bottle of water that came with deal. never ever again!
I had a relatively decent vegetarian burger for lunch here. They do really good package deals I had chips & a coke with it for around $10 I think it was. The service was also friendly & fast
Bloody Horrible- thick gluggy batter on tasteless fish. Probably the worst I have ever had. Couldn't find calamari in the calamari rings.
A better fried food outlet than the one next door. At least at lunchtime the food tastes freshly fried and the chips fresh! My pick if you need something greasy!
Disgusting! The calamari wasn't even squid, some gross fish mince. The fish was undercooked and the batter was eggy and stodgey. Old and inedible. AVOID!

Food was I edible. Thought we would try this place for lunch. Food was terrible. Anyone who knows me knows I like my food. I had calamari and chips. I don't know what was in the breadcrumbs but is didn't taste a thing like calamari. It was just mush and the chips were only ordinary too. Never going back. No use saying anything only young people serving with not a care
So simply crap. The end
Horrible, inedible food

Went here for a weekday lunch with the parents. Ordered the Aussie Parmigiana, which consisted of crispy and moist chicken schnitzel with a slice of ham and melted cheese. Simple and filling to eat. The accompanying sauce, however, was overly sweet. Service was friendly and reasonably efficient. Casual ambience with indoor and outdoor seating available. Reasonable prices. Overall, a casual and average lunch option whilst shopping at Brisbane Airport DFO.

Disappointing. Dirty table which I had to request to be cleaned. They were out of white rice for a curry dish I ordered and I lost track of how long I waited. I ordered the spicy special. Now I like hot food but this was ridiculously hot. Disappointing all around.

Yeahh to free coffee. The Coffee Club on Albert Street was offering free coffee all day today. Got my Chai Latte around 1ish and even they have been flat out since morning they were still friendly and polite. Yes they were busy but the wait time wasn't long. I even saw them grab customers to another counter to serve them faster. They had a good fast system going and my chai latte was perfect. Really happy and impressed.

One of the better Coffee Clubs I have visited in the CBD. I think it has recently undergone a renovation? Ordered a double shot flat white & it was delivered promptly to the table, very well presented with no bitterness. Coffee had a smooth finish. Service very good

Standard coffee. The coffee club was a good first time experience. I really liked the location more than their coffee. I went along with a couple of my friends who are not a great lover of coffee, so obviously their opinion doesn't matter but still fyi, they said that the cofee was 'really nice'. To sum it up, its an okay coffee by the busy street.
This is equal parts tourist trap and a city worker's last resort. If actually like coffee and want food that's been prepared by a trained cook or chef, go almost anywhere else in the CBD.

'Big Breakfast': bacon, 2 poached eggs, grilled tomatos and mushrooms, pork and sage chipolatas, baked beans and a hash brown, served with toasted ciabatta. 'Salmon & Avo Stack': smoked salmon served with two baked corn and zuccini fritters, topped with avocado, dill and onion ricotta, a poached egg and baby spinach. Wasnt exactly a stack that i expected at all. Was quite disappointed in both presentation and taste; super bland

Pleasant atmosphere, lovely lunch options and smooth coffee despite being overpriced. Delicious toasties and amazing large chip helpings. The desserts in the window are so tantalizing. I will be coming back.

Staff was very rude and they don't know what they are serving. It was freezing sitting outside table so I asked one girl whether I could move inside and she got annoyed that I'm moving. No idea why she was annoyed. The food portion was so small. I ordered granola bowl and I could even make it better at home. Horrible. Never come back here. Train your staff properly. Very rude.

My husband and I came here last Thursday for brunch (approx 11am). We entered the store from the front (side entrance available) and the barista instantly acknowledged us and asked us to take a seat. We sat at a table against the wall, plates were left there from a previous diner but there wasn't a better seating area (most available was under ceiling fans and I was feeling a little cold). We were starving, I had previously been to a fasting blood test which took 3 hours and by this point I could eat a horse (not literally)! After waiting a good 5-10 mins for a waitstaff and menus, my husband approached the counter to ask/ grab some menus so that we could order straight away when a staff member was available. The barista said, "take a seat and we'll bring it to you", my husband insisted on a menu but the barista again said we'll bring it to you. there were 2 female waitstaff serving tables and 1 male waitstaff serving drinks and taking takeaway orders. Another 10mins went by and we were ready to walk out! Staff were just chatting to each other at one point and finally when a waitstaff had to serve drinks to the table next to us we "waved her down", by saying "excuse me". And she instantly said I'll come and clear your table. We replied, and asked for menus. She took our drinks order and soon after we had to wave another staff down to place an order. We ordered the Salmon & Avo Stack, Bacon, Eggs & Tomato and a side of chips. Why the random chips? I had cravings for deep fried potatoes and was going to opt for the hash brown but at $3 a pop and wanting more than 1, I thought I'd get more potatoes for the side of chips at $7.90! The food came after 15-20mins and by this point I was starving! It tasted good (or I was just so hungry everything tasted good)! The bacon was a little oily but otherwise a decent serving size. We finished our meal within 10mins! Overall, the customer service could have been a little better. The food was alright, but the CBD could offer me a better experience with similar food.
A reliable coffee stop while on walkabout at Mt Ommaney Shopping Centre. The large Cafe Latte is served hot and is full flavoured. A good coffee!

I had my breakfast this morning here. The quality of the food was great. The lady who served me at the counter was Louise. She was just amazing. Even she come and asked me how was the food and if everything is alright. I was very impressed with her great service and friendly attitude

Just stopped for a coffee and cake on Sunday afternoon. The counter staff were pleasant and I give the coffee about a 8 out of 10, but the accompaniments were mediocre. Both the biscuit and the carrot cake were a bit stale. The lady at the table behind us told the waiter that she ordered her sandwich on Turkish bread when he brought it to her, and so he took it back rolling his eyes - not her fault they messed up the order. Won't be back.

With Mt Omm as my "local" and many a breakfast at various places in the Centre, the one place I don't find myself going all that often is the Shingle Inn.  Not sure why, as when I do go I usually enjoy it.  Perhaps its because I still have such fond memories of the original on Edward St in the city, it's dark cool mysteriousness (well in my memory of over 30 years ago), and the outlets that have popped up in the various shopping centre's around Brisbane just seem a little wrong! Anyway, I found myself at Shingle Inn a few weeks back on my Friday off and decided to enjoy a late brunch there.  A mug of flat white and a bacon and egg wrap with a hash brown included in the wrap (you can have it as a side or inside the wrap) were my order and both were delicious.  I have to say the coffee here is always good - great flavour, nice and hot, not too bitter.  And the wrap was good - I usually have the hash brown on the side - so being a little adventurous was great and I really like the inclusion. I should go here more often!

Great breakfast of waffles with ice cream and caramel sauce, and an omelet with sweet potato, spinach, cheese and pinenuts. We had bowls of coffee too which were pretty decent! Get in early to get the comfy chairs up the back.

Extremely disappointing service. I booked a high tea sitting for 3 people on Mother's Day 3 weeks in advance because I knew that it may be busy. I was assured of a corner booth by the owner Nikki who confirmed the booking and I explained to her that my mother was elderly and not able to sit on any other seats. I popped into the store one week prior, to reconfirm the booking and told the staff again about the corner booth which they reconfirmed was reserved for me. On Mothers Day when we arrived the owner told me he had given the corner booth to a walk-in customer and that we could have the bench seats instead! Of course I walked out very disappointed and wont patronise this store again. Thank you Shingle Inn Mt Ommaney for spoiling Mother's Day! Dont take bookings in advance if you dont intend to keep them! This type of service is very unprofessional!

I went to the Shingle Inn at Mt Om on Saturday Jan 31 for lunch with two of my daughters. The food took a long time to come out and when it did it was COLD when it was meant to be HOT. I ordered Eggs Benedict London and was so so so disappointed I did not want to eat it but I had already paid - I did think about wrapping it up to take home to my dogs but then I changed my mind. The ham was a processed ham not shaved as in the menu description. The hollandaise sauce tasted liked melted butter - it was horrible. My daughters both ordered Avocado Smashed and it was meant to be sourdough bread but got wholemeal instead - the entire meal was COLD when it was meant to be HOT. VERY VERY VERY DISAPPOINTED AND WILL NEVER GO TO THIS CAFE AGAIN OR RECOMMEND IT TO ANYONE.

Food is precooked, frozen and then reheated. As shown by the puddles of water under the frittatas. They heated the cakes up as well and I've never experienced that at any other shingle inns in Queensland or New South Wales and they didn't ask if we would like them heated. Asked for no sauce or no nothing on sour dough bread but they slathered it with butter instead to the point there were chunks of butter on the lettuce as well. Disappointing given I've only had good food at all other shingle inn.

Great service. I often frequent this shingle inn when I'm in the area and am always struck by how friendly the staff are. But what really impressed me were how helpful they were with catering for an event last November. The lady involved was fantastic, and able to give me in depth phone advice to help me place my order ( I don't know many places that would give me the time she did), and of the sandwiches provided for the high tea were lovely, and complimented by all. Highly recommended, especially for catering,

WILL NEVER RETURN (MT OM). This place is the biggest disappointment. People go there expecting to have a nice cup of tea or coffee and cake on the big couches - don't be fooled. Your better off going down to coffee club (hate to admit it) for a better experience. ALSO - way overpriced.
The flavours are sensational, that's why we keep coming back. Love your style.
I don't know why there are so many bad reviews.  We've been eating here since it opened and have never had a bad meal.  Perhaps people have too many different expectations of what Thai should be.

Love it! Albeit on the fringe of Wynnum in some regard there is plenty of parking, and the service is fantastic. The food is well priced and always perfect. The atmosphere to dine in is quaint and very comfortable but equally given it's location it's a breeze to grab takeaway from on the way home. We really love this as our quiet 'date night' local.

Went here for a friends birthday. Service was abysmal. They didn't have our table ready, so hurriedly shoved us in the corner. And then proceeded to ignore us for half an hour. We had to get up and ask for water, and then get up again to see if we could order. Two other groups came in after us, and the were given water immediately, and had their order taken in a timely manner. The food was below average. Tasted like supermarket curry paste. Would never go back.

Admittedly, can be a hit & miss affair. Standard Thai food have had good & bad here. Cannot go wrong with the vegetarian stir fries though, which is what I usually order. Never had a problem with service

Ordered a takeaway dinner from this place. Very disappointed. We ordered the chefs choice chilli fish which was battered and fried fish in a sweet chilli sauce with capsicum and other veggies. The fish tasted too dry.

Good tasty Thai tucker here campers ;) often have the lunch special in-house or have delivery hero drop off dinner always nice and with good body not just the watery sauce one often gets at other establishments.

Used to be a regular here but have been disappointed of late. Restaurant doesn't seat that many people so gets very noisy and cramped. Last visit we were seated at a table with a dirty tablecloth, took 10 minutes to be brought crockery and menus - then watched an ant crawl over my plate. Have also seen large cockroaches run through the restaurant - reflected in their food safety rating. Food is not bad, but portion sizes have declined.

Mays Thai Wynnum - A local favourite. So many mixed reviews, I am surprised, we live locally and to date have never had a bad take away or eat in meal there, always accommodating for our large family of 8, including a vegan, vegetarian and meat eaters. Never had a problem in a year. Understandably waited for a while due to a full restaurant, but honestly struggling with these negative reviews, the staff can never do enough for us. ---24 Mar, 2015--- Mays Thai Wynnum - A local favourite. So many mixed reviews, I am surprised, we live locally and to date have never had a bad take away or eat in meal there, always accommodating for our large family of 8, including a vegan, vegatarian and meat eaters. Never had a problem in a year. Understandably waited for a while due to a full restaurant, but honestly struggling with these negative reviews, the staff can never do enough for us.

Hello. Im a regular customer. ordered online . no good , called up and paid, no good , called again to check my order as it went over the time for delivery. no good. very . very disappointed ~ U Charge my credit card u have another thing coming !]

Great ambience, good food. Loved that there were 2 sizes of pizza, which were hot and delicious. Vegetarians well catered for & salad was fresh with good dressing. Good to hear live music on a Monday night.

Big fan of the Burrow. Have been for both breakfast and dinner here. The "screen door" is one of my favourite meals. The burrow also has some good craft beer options, good music and friendly staff and service.

I absolutely loved this place! Such a cool restaurant with really friendly staff and delicious food. You can tell that The Burrow has a real sense of originality by its atmosphere but also how they make everything on their menu in house like the dips and the burger patties. It was really hard for me to choose only two things from the menu because all their vegan options looked so yummy! The pizza that I had was gone too quickly because it was just too good, crispy crust and flavourful topping, should of ordered a bigger one! The dips that we ordered tasted very flavourful and you could tell that the chefs takepride in what they make and how they make things. Will definitely be ordering some of these dips for my birthday! Overall this place has got to be one of my go to restaurants in Brisbane now that I have tried only a fraction of their amazing vegan food options. I went during lunch time so I look forward to go there for dinner and seeing the place buzzing!

The food is really delicious and totally surprised us . The fries is crispy outside and the texture of the pizza base is really crispy as well. Just the beef of the burger is a bit smaller. I am a person who would seldom go back to have same restaurant again but i would go back to The Burrow for definitely.

This place is excellent. While I loved their old venue, this one is also fun. It was a bit bizarre at first as I had friends who lived in that house many moons ago but now it’s one of my favourite spots for lunch. Love that there are heaps of vegan options and add ons- You can swap regular cheese for vegan etc. The beetroot pizza is epic and such bang for buck. So are the nachos- I’ve had both the vegan and normal nachos. I love sour cream a lot so the normal win for me-

Completely agree with the reviewer who said this place feels like a student sharehouse/op shop/café. However, once you get over the fact that I'm definitely not cool enough to eat here, the food is delicious. One of the only places in Brisbane that you can get poutine. And that, my friends, is why I've been back three times.

Wanted to treat my friend out for dinner on her birthday and she picked the burrow as the dine in spot! It’s a vibrant place with chalk art, craft beers and creative pizzas. The staff was very friendly and check on us a few times, great vibe and an enjoyed an wonderful night out with good food and plenty of D&Ms!

This place kind of feels like a student share house mixed with an opp shop and café. Could have walked by and missed it if I wasn't looking for it. I got a veggie burger with sweet potato chips and the boyf got something with meat. We both liked the food, the staff were friendly and the atmosphere was nice and chill, the only let down was the coffee we had afterwards. All in all a nice lunch though.
Superb iced long black and perfect places to curl up with a book. I highly recommend seating out back downstairs in the garden. Also the screen door breakfast is just indulgent!

Having already eaten at a nearby restaurant (Govindas - see my review ) we were in search a cosy quiet place to have a nice hot drink on a pretty cold night, and we discovered this little Gem of a spot. NB : My review is for hot drinks and service NOT food. The Service was friendly and welcoming , my friends drinks were hot and delicious and my soy chai Latte was one of the best I had ever had ! The young lady behind the bar was happy to share who and where it came from and I am happy to find out it is very local ! We shall be back for food. Thanks SARDS.
I’m never disappointed with our local Grill’d. Good food and good staff. Everything is always cooked just right and I love their seeded bread rolls

I love the garden goodness burger, it's hard to find a good veggo burger and this one is so good i get cravings for it. I've been here a few times now and they are consistent with quality. Friendly staff, relaxed atmosphere, quality food 🍴

Food is extremely slow. Waiters and waitresses just chatted to each other instead of actually preparing food. No food served for ages. Customers waited and waited and waited It unfortunate that the lowest star the app has is 1 star, I would totally think it could be minus 5 stars.
Do try thier big Queenslander beef burger with fries . It was too big to handle but the taste was extremely good . Very friendly staff with good ambience .
Ordered a clean n green salad with chicken breast and it was so burnt I could barely enjoy the salad itself. Chips were perfect and im so glad I ordered them to make up for the salad

Boyfriend went to collect our burgers and fries after ordering over the phone on Sunday late morning. It had been 15 mins by the time he left to pick it up and it wasn't ready even though they said it would be. The staff were apparently very chatty and not very observant of what they were doing. This proved right as when my partner went back 5 mins later the meals still weren't ready, so he went to the shop and then they finally were ready once he got back. Got home, his order was wrong - asked for bacon and got a beef patty. My burger was thankfully right, but the sweet potato fries were obviously quite burnt. P.S. $9 for a "large" sweet potato fries when it looked like a small to medium at best is ridiculous
How can you go wrong with a burger when you can get amazing craft beer to wash it down. The sweet potato fries were a little dry though. The chilli on the burger blew my head off but I enjoyed it.

My new favorite burger from Grilld is the Nourish & Flourish on the low carb bun. The bun has a really nice slight coconut flavor and is a nice change from the regular buns. Grilld might not service the cheapest burgers in town but there burgers are always constantly good!

This grill'd is part of a plaza so it's good if you're a local but otherwise it would be a nicer setting to visit another store. This time I ordered the goats cheese and hummus burger which was yummy. They have astro turf outside with hanging lights. My friends ordered the spicy burger but it had way too much sour cream which just dripped out and made a big mess.

I am always very satisfied with my grill'd orders wherever I go, but I have to say, I was most disappointed with Grill'd Newmarket. My burger was definitely smaller than normal and it tasted a little bit cold. I was happy with the service at the start, although while myself and my partner were eating our meal we kept having the same waitress bugging us to take our plate, was a little annoying. I will try this place again soon, but if it turns out the same again, I will go back to Grill'd Rosalie.
Been here a couple of times. Fantastic food, service and atmosphere. Highly recommend!
Fantastic food and great service! The complimentary chocolates were a nice surprise. The staff are very friendly and accommodating. We will definitely be back soon!

Amazing fresh food, lovely accommodating staff, great atmosphere, good menu selection! The fairy lights out the front create such a cute and quaint vibe travel here from inner city for the pizza 10/10 would recommend
Loved the high quality food, the large pizza and salad can feed a hungry couple. Also amazing service where you can BYO! Will be back again. Thanks so much

Very impressive local Italian restaurant. Mark who is the Host has a real commitment to service and when we arrived we felt very welcome. We started off with the bruschetta, which was nice and fresh, and it was great that even though we ordered 1 serving, there was 3 pieces which was one each. Mains arrived around 15 minutes later which was perfect timing. I had the Greek Salad, my wife had the fettuccine with chicken and my son had the large pizza. All agreed that the meals were excellent. Great food, service and atmosphere. I highly recommend it.

Best pizzas on the southside! The shop is tucked away but once you get there you won't be disappointed. The boys running the show are extremely friendly, funny and genuinely put love in the food they make. No matter what I've ordered always been pleased and keep coming back ❤

Fabulous food, great ambience, young friendly happy staff. BYO The food is fresh, tasty and made on the premises . no bought in lasagnes or pastas ! The wood fire pizzas are thin crust & delicious. made fresh for you whilst you wait, the best on the south side of Brisbane 🙌

Disappointing tonight. We pay $35 for a large Calabrese, and normally it's worth every cent, but tonight's pizza was horrible. Smaller than usual, no ricotta and the base tasted like cardboard. Sooooo disappointed. We're regular customers and we want to come back so I hope this is just a one off mistake of a pizza, and not the result of some permanent change to recipe or method.
Food was great. dont expect much different products on pizzas. italian pizzas. Good service. garlic bread was different to what i expected but still very nice. Enjoy every mouthful.

Where my pasta lovers at? I was craving pasta tonight and nothing else would suffice so I did a quick search on Google and came across this place literally 5 minutes drive from home. After reading a few reviews on how great the pizza was I thought I'd give the place a go. I'm so glad I did! I've found it near impossible to find decent pasta (especially takeaway) anywhere in Brisbane. So stoked I found this little gem so close to home! Would have given a 5 if it wasn't for the wait to get my food, but it was totally worth it and the staff were very friendly. Will be back very soon. Second visit. We ate in this time. We ordered the lamb pizza which was devine, and a small between the two of us was the perfect amount for an entree. For mains I ordered the seafood fettuccine. After asking what seafood was in it and being advised it had muscles I was going to change my selection, but the owner said he could make it without muscle which I appreciate as alot of places wont do that. My partner ordered the mushroom & blue cheese penne. Both were beautiful. Pasta cooked perfectly and both sauces were rich and super tasty. The meals came out super quick this time too. Great place.

For the first time, I tried Mexican food At Guzman y Gomez and I absolutely loved it. It is a place that I always go back there however the self service section, can be more organised e.g always there is rotten coriander in the container.

Although not the best mexican food, guzman has never disappointed me. This time I ordered spicy grilled steak enchiladas (large$15.5). The taste was acceptable, steak and rice were well made, the enchilada was well prepared.

This place was my first every experience with Guzman Y Gomez back in 2012 when I saw a massive line for free burritos. Ever since then I have been hooked and Guzman Y Gomez in general is my go to Mexican restaurant. This has also been my local GYG since then the the quality, consistency and service has never dropped and I have never been disappointed.

I really like this Guzman. Food is identical to the rest of the chains but I enjoy the service here - even when they are swamped they seem to process everyone quickly. Easy, fast, predictable shopping centre food.

My everyday Go to. Being a vegetarian, options of delicious yet veg food are very rare in australia. But these Veg Nachos with extra hot sauce is my staple. Such fresh ingredients and the tangy sauces never go wrong. Quick service, fun music, yum yum mexican food. The perfect everyday meal. Burritos and nachos here are the best. Dont even aim for quesadillas though, they come in such small portions you might not even know when you finished them. All in all, grab that extra cheese and guacamole. Wont regret ever. 😊

Pretty good, though I found the nachos heavy and thick with cheese, so I couldn't finish all of it. I recommend asking for no cheese on top, as you will most likely feel heavy afterwards. But excepting that, I did enjoy my meal, especially in their modern - but - Mexican setting, with layers of cacti serving as walls.

100% my favourite Mexican place and nothing can beat it. Come here once a week to get my all time fave the enchilada. The lady who is there frequently has even remembered my order. Could not be any more happy with how fast their service is and the quality of their food. Could not recommend this place anymore !
Love this place. I order through Deliveroo and the food is always great Beef burrito is a winner and the fries are tasty. Honestly can't fault the food I have got from here at all

{uid:37351257} and {uid:37351290} brought home burritos from Guzman y Gomez for dinner tonight. We shared the Spicy Steak, a Slow-Cooked Beef and a Little Guy Chicken Burrito. With the exception of the Little Guy, it was hard to discern whether they had remembered to add cheese to the burritos. The flavours were good, but a little muted compared to what I've come to expect from other outlets. The Little Guy Chicken was also quite dry. I really like GYG, and they usually rate 3.5-4, but this was not quite up to their usual standards.

This GYG has very generous serves. I got my usual nachos with spicy pulled pork and it was a huge serve. Service is friendly and efficient as expected. The only downer was that the salsa bar was not well stocked, it was mostly empty and the coriander had seen better days. That said we visited after the lunch rush (2pm) so perhaps it had just been cleaned out by hungry lunchers.

I have eaten at most of the GyG outlets across Brisbane and this one appears to be the best for consistently decent flavour on their spicy chicken options I usually get. My only complaint though is that sometimes they taste a bit too salty which their nutritional info confirms with their stroke inducing levels of sodium across all their range.

This place serves authentic mexican food. I had burrito bowl and quesadillas. Both were outstanding and messy with hot sauce. This restro has a range of sauce from mild spicy to very hot. Mexican food is known for its messyness, that is what it makes the food taste so great because at the finish of your meal you always endup licking your fingertips.

I've been to this Guzman y Gomez location several times and have never had a bad meal. Usually I stick to the slow cooked beef (Beef Guerrero) burritos, but it was early and I was interested to learn that the also serve breakfast. I went with the Breakfast Burrito with Bacon ($5.95) and a side Hashbrown ($1). Great value and good flavour. The hashbrown was a bit greasy and both the one in my burrito and the one I ordered on the side were a bit cool. Otherwise, great.

I wouldn't have had beef with my meal at good ol Guzman had my burrito been put together like a burrito, as in Mexican goodness wrapped in a tortilla. It took a while to make, and by the time I'd unwrapped the foil there was burrito everywhere. I would expect it from a 2am kebab run, but maybe not for a $12 burrito.

We finally gave gomez a go to try it out. What a mistake! My mind was on the fish tacos as some other Mex places dont offer it. So i was really looking forward to it. I ordered 3 tacos: 1 steak & pork chipotle & the barramundi taco. Staff seemed very unorganised with the menu as customers were receiving the wrong items so in seeing that i made sure my order was correct. Upon chomping down my tacos i was sooo utterly disappointed. It was bland & the taco toritallas tasted stale. Not worth it my money was worth spending somewhere else

Spicy chicken. Have had the spicy chicken burrito a few times. Would be good if they spread the spicy meat through the rice instead of having a big dollop at one end. The burrito with the extras was filling and tasty but watch out that you don't get a mouthful of spicy meat.
Once again. Usual slop. Too much rice. No filling. Rubbish.
Bonza Burritos. Had a few of the Steak Burritos from this and some of the other GyGs. Always tasty. not sure if it's worth paying extra for the Avo, but still good.
Spicy burrito bowl with brown rice & avo - very tasty! Is substantial so hardly ate the rice but it's great they offer that option.
Great flavourful quick food. Spicy means spicy. Filling but not sickening. Recommend spicy chicken - tasty!

First time visiting Australia and what better way than to spend an afternoon shopping and having few beers, tacos and tortillas 😍 which I can’t get back at home, the ambience is superb, fast service and quality food, would highly recommend to try out if ya’ll want to spice up with the mexico cuisine. Looking forward to visit again
This is one of my fav lunch places.  I am a huge fan of their new Cali Burrito. It's the perfect taste for me.  Goes their at least once a week.

I ordered Mini Nachos with Chicken because the Regular size is too big for me, always coming here everytime I visit Brisbane. All ingredients fresh, add free for Onion, Jalapeños. One of must do Brisbane 😋

love the food! guess it would’ve been nicer if it the nacho fries were actually a combo of corn chips and fries like i thought they were 😰 but anyway, the food was still good. always a great place to come for mexican food. ambience is good too. thankfully the place isn’t too dark to take good pics of food, but still maintains a nice spacious feel about it. staff were friendly as well.

Despite a line to order around dinnertime, still fast and efficient service! Ingredients were fresh in our burrito bowls (barramundi and chicken). However not sure if they have MSG flavour enhancers in the food since I was quite thirsty for a few hours afterwards. Lovely and spacious interior with many tables to eat at. Quality is consistent across all branches :)

GYG is my go to fast food Mexican. Always consistent in quality, flavour and service in all their stores. My absolute favourite thing to order are their nachos, either with chicken or pulled pork. I've tried every item on their menu and nothing tops the Nachos.
I love GYG! Regular customer here :) you guys deserve a 5 star rating for the best customer service and quality food. Keep it up! Free range chicken! Beating the fast food industry!

This place is bustling and busy and looks like it's run pretty well. In a pretty great location in the CBD, just a short stroll from the Queens Street mall down the little lane that is that part of Albert Street. Sure, it's Mexican themed fast food, but it sure can hit the spot when you're looking for a quick lunchtime fill-up! A tad overpriced but the food usually tastes pretty fresh and is served quickly, which is what I look for in a fast food chain.
It is ok,but I may not come here again to eat due to not attractive enough.In conclusion,here can be such a place where you want to resolve your hungry problem.

Guzman Y Gomez was honestly one of my favourite options when eating out, and as a vegan it is one of only a few. I usually have no problems with the food and service although last night was very different! I ordered my usual meatless, dairyless nachos only to find various bits of chicken throughout! This however wouldn't have been a problem if it had been resolved, but when I took the nachos back I got the response of a mere "Sorry, we're busy, it happens." and my nachos were merely taken away and not replaced. So for $15 I had gotten a bottle of water and no nachos.  I am very unhappy with my experience and unfortunately will not be going back!

caption.text: The Crown Hotel - L&B Meatball Sandwich
The Crown Hotel - Low and Slow Burger Range

review.text: I would like to give this hotel a quarter of a star and thats being generous. A couple of months ago around june my partner and i on holidays decided to give this hotel a try as it was not far from our hotel but what a huge mistake this was, we arrived around 6.40m and decided to ordered some food from the menu that looked really great as we waited my partner and i dec@ided to play 20 dollars in the pokies. After a hour i asked the lovley girl behind the bar if the meals would be ready soon, she went to check. As it turned out our order had somhow got lost between the casheir and the kitchen she apologised and got her manager by now its almost 9and the manager who was a tall ,older ladie with dark hair and a was very rude and snaped that the kitchen is not taking any more orders and she did not care that we had ordered and paid at for our meals. She called my partner a smartass when he asked for a refund for the meal we did not receive. She was very aggressive and angry over a problem that could have been handled in a more professional way. She also called us snobs and asked us to leave. Its the worst experience ive ever encounted. She should not work or especially manage@ a hotel at any hour when you must engage with people in a hospitable way. I will tell everyone to avoid this crown hotel at lutwyche from now on, i hope the day manager has more tact and a ability to deal and talk to customers.

Great value for money and decent food came as a real surprise for me at The Crown. From the outside, this place really lacks curb appeal. It needs a refresh because it's actually got great food! Inside is better but still a little dull. We ordered lunch and it came quickly. I had the pulled pork burger which was tasty - really good soft bun and a generous amount of pork. Pork wasn't the best I've ever had but still tasty. The chips were really crispy and yum and a great aioli dipping sauce. My husband had the steak sandwich which he really enjoyed (and the man is a steak sandwich lover). There are plenty of drinks to choose from (not a lot of great craft beer though) and wine specials for $5 a glass are always welcome. The food isn't totally amazing but my score is based on value for money and judging it for what it is. A bit of a refresh and this place would be a great local that I'd visit again.
Incredibly underrated - still haven't had a bad meal. It's a lunch work staple with great prices considering the range of burgers, specials, etc.
The crown is so underrated. We haven't had a bad meal here yet. It is our go to chicken parmi establishment. Food is out quick and fresh, also tasty. I don't know why more people don't come here.
The best grilled herbed Barra I've had in a long time. Topped with a lovely salad. Had friendly staff. I was quite pleased in trying this venue.

Not a bad lunch for $14. Myself and a mate got the chicken parmigana. Wasn't the best i'd had but was satisfying enough for a quick lunch. Would like to try more of the menu as i feel they would have better dishs there.

VEGETARIANS EXIST. Hey, I know you're a pub but sometimes a leafy salad just doesn't cut it. You used to have options for us veggos - guess I'll just go to the Albion instead. Shame, because your food was actually pretty nice until I couldn't eat anything anymore. Won't return unless you cater for people living in this century. Not everyone wants a hunk of cow. Ya feel me bro?

The Crowning Disappointment. Pathetic. Its the best i have to say. Marginal food at the best of times. The new moron of a manager has recently decided to leave all the doors open not only rendering the air con useless on a hot day but also as the front door is on a very busy road so there is traffic noise through the entire establishment. Absolute genius. To add insult to this we were still planning to do a Christmas lunch as it is our local and in spite of a printed menu and numerous conversations plus a firm booking we turn up only to find the place all closed up. We were not the only ones. Very professional. A phone call was not possible it seems as they are too busy and important to care about customers. Well that has fixed us we will not be back. What a bunch of idiots.

Generally empty venue, even on weekends. Food, for the most part is good. I don't want to write a negative review about the menu or the food, or even the people. I've had one negative experience out of many, but it's enough to discourage me from returning again. I ordered a takeaway vegetarian pizza, walked the two streets home and took a bite. I realised that it was covered in pesto and being allergic to most nuts, started vomiting. I called the Crown Hotel to explain what had happened and asked that if I brought it back, would I be able to get one without the pesto, as I'm allergic to nuts. The person on the phone hesitantly said "okay". I got to the hotel and sat down near the bar where I originally ordered the pizza. A man who I presume to be the manager came out and asked me if I ordered the pizza. I responded yes and handed him the full box with one piece of the original pizza missing and said "I'm sorry, it seems like such a waste". To my surprise, the man grunted and said "you know, normally you would have to pay for another one. It says on the menu that it has nuts" I explained that I hadn't seen the menu and had simply asked if they had any vegetarian pizzas. He showed me the menu and it did say that it contained 'pesto mayo', but no mention of any nuts. Now, I understand that it was my mistake for not looking at the menu or asking the wait staff if it contained any nuts, my reason for this is because my allergy is mild, and not anaphylactic, so my life is not at risk if I consume nuts. My shock comes from the way it was handled. I was not rude or demanding on the phone, I made no demands, I only asked, I didn't argue, I didn't scold them. Yet I was met with the attitudes that I was trying to rip them off or act shady with one piece of my pizza was eaten. If I pay $17.00 for a pizza, I'm going to damn well get something that I can digest. If I was dining in and something was wrong with my meal, I'm sure I wouldn't have been met with the rudeness and attitude that I was tonight. Once again, to reiterate: the bar/wait staff are wonderful, the venue is nice, the food tastes good, there's never anybody there, but apparently the manager is a wanker.

Diana. Thought we would go out of our comfort zone & try pub grub for a change at The Crown which looks good after the reno (dont know when that was incidently) We had a voucher deal for this adventure into the burbs which included a glass of wine & $10 pokie credit entre & mains. The entre was pretty basic fare, an asian tasting plate, which seemed to me like was frozen & fried (like those mixed bags in the supermarket freezers) The brushetta bread we had was quite good (maybe the best dish of the night!) For the mains we had two fish dishes, I had the grilled fish with salad & beer battered fries which was not bad apart from the one piece of fish being a bit rubbery, the partner had a mixed selection which he too thought was OK. The charming waiter who served the food was just so sweet, but the best part of the night was when we went to use our gaming credit & a rude woman got stroppy when I accidently sat in her chair, evidently this poker machine stuff is taken very seriously so if you happen to go to the Crown do not nick someones seat! LOL
Ordered via UberEats and it was disgusting. so disappointed. The brownie desert wasn’t even cooked. nothing like the photos at all. Price was extremely high as well not good value for money

Bun Mobile has been around for a while. I find their fillings very wholesome and their service is enthusiastic. I remember trying to chase their location on a clunky website :D Verdict: Asian street food for white people.
Can't go wrong with the bun mobile. So tasty! I love the vibe they have and they are always friendly and laid back. Keen to check them out at their next location.
So delicious! Been three times and each time is perfect! The brownies are also really good :) good amount of menu items and I've seen new flavour combinations each time I've been.

Cino's appraisal: •Chicken & shroom - tender chook, juicy bacon. Purring and chewing together at last. •Bbq pork - frenzied reowing and climbing up legs gets me more tidbits. Eyes rolling back in head. •Wagyu beef - kitty belly almost full. •Chicken wings - snoring from bed only. Beware the litter tray tmr mum. but thanks for sharing 😻

I am always excited when I turn up for an event and one of the two Bun Mobiles is there.  Everything is so tender and delicious.  My wife used to stalk them around the city - not only does she love their food, but when there was a worldwide Siracha shortage a few years ago they could always be counted on to have plenty of the spicy goodness.

I really don't get the cult following the Bun Mobile has created. The flavor of the buns was ok but the presentation was bad, it looked like it had just been quickly thrown together. The price is very high for what you receive and at $10 a bun, I was very disappointed. I may have had a one-off bad experience as I have friends who love this place so I would probably check out it again in the future.

user.profile_name: Slick Chef Extraordinaire. Gangster Of Food.

review.text: This is seriously the best mobile food truck, not only do you receive superior customer service, the food is amazing. Favourites are the Chicken Caesar and the Lamb.

I am not sure I agree with the outpouring of admiration for Bun. I'd like to think that I had a one-off experience. I can't however, share the same level of enthusiasm for Bun that others seem to display. I "get" that the Mantou style steamed bun might be a novelty for some but it's not anything new. I appreciate the mixing of food styles might cause some excitement too. I ordered the chicken and I can tell you it was like "that" picture of food where the photo gets you excited and the actual product leaves a lot to be desired. When working with flavours like Bun do, less is more. All I tasted was Mantou bun, a piece of chicken (not cooked very well) and Hoi Sin sauce accompanied with some shavings of cabbage, a strand of carrot a little else. It was put together very badly and the construct of flavours was completely overpowered by Hoi Sin sauce. I am sure Bun are doing something right but as a complete fan of Asian flavours I am getting a little tired of "near enough is good enough" being peddled as something "unique". All in all, a completely poor experience and 10.00 for what I ate amounts to robbery! I'll try Bun again but it's very over-hyped and over priced.
Dinner here tonight at kangaroo point with the family, best buns I've had in Brisbane, quality and freshness 110% great friendly service, cant wait to catch up again! Thanks

I lucked out and got in just after the lunch rush, so the food was fresh and hot; but the staff were a bit stressed, however they were still friendly. The food was standard, pleasant but uninteresting. If you feel like KFC you could do worse. I would recommend.
Mmmmmmm. Hungry dawg must eat KFC. mmmmm. woof woof woof.

caption.text: Chinese cake with rice cake filling

review.text: The shop is hiding and doesn’t look fancy, but it made the best cheesecake I’ve ever had. Fresh mango cake ?! So good ! Those two are my favorites. They have other cakes too but not as good as cheese cake and fresh mango cake :)

This bakery sells variants of breads, cookies (even eggless cookies), and cakes. I was interested in their chinese cake. It was written that the cake had coconut and rice cake fillings. Since I love rice cake, so I didnt mind giving it a try. The outer part of the cake was crunchy. It was similar as puff pastry. The inner part was moist, chewy and soft. It was the rice cake which gave such texture. It tasted just right, not too sweet so I could enjoy it. It was good and cheap as well. 2.40$ for one cake. However I couldnt taste the coconut, (I expected to taste the shredded coconut along with the rice cake as the filling) I wasnt sure if it was supposed to be two kinds of chinese cake with different filling or one chinese cake with a filling of combination of coconut and rice cake.

Was intending to pay a visit to my Indian grocery store around the corner from here to find it had closed after 30 years of trade! Saw this place was rather dubious about the coffee but as it turned out I was pleasantly surprised. Coffee was Robert Timms & was really smooth & strong without the double shot. Cake of the day was tiramisu, delicately moist coffee liqueur sponge with layers of rich custard. Very pleasant staff & excellent prices

As for the cake itself, I absolutely loved it. I found the texture to be far smoother but lighter than the other asian cakes I've had, and the Cake:Cream:Fruit ratio to be near perfect. The fruit was really fresh and sweet. Its noteworthy that the owner didnt sell me the mango cake because they were not certain they would get ripe sweet mangoes, I found this to be very ethical and refreshing in a commercial context.
Best Coffee roll in Brisbane! I gotta repeat. The best!!
NewYork Cheese cake ← Must try
Thank you Cheung's. Your banana cake was fresh, moist, tasty and at $7.50 I almost can't make it for that.

Sacher Torte that blew my mind!. My love and I attend this quirky place as regularly as possible - it's a special romantic spot for us, where we share a pot of tea, or a coffee and an Asian bakery item in peace. Often there are one or two interesting Valley characters hanging out but mostly it is very quiet. Where can you get a pot of tea for two for $2-70? On a whim one day I bought a Sacher Torte from the display and almost immediately regretted it. Why would an Asian bakery know how to make a Sacher Torte? How wrong could we be - best Sacher Torte ever - moist liqueur centre, fresh chocolate cake and icing. Sensational!

Pretty disappointing experience. I had heard so much about this place and was really expecting to like it. We had a booking for 7:45, and the table that we were eventually sat at was empty from the time we arrived. We however had to wait until 8:20 before we were seated. While we waited at the bar, we ordered French martini’s. The cocktails were extremely watered down with pineapple juice and were very disappointing for the price. The bar staff were generally not very friendly either. At dinner, we were never given 2 of the dishes we ordered, but did not realise until we had already gone home. Service was pretty non existent all night. The food we did receive was good, but not good enough to make up for everything else. I was just pretty disappointed with the whole experience. Considering that this place is not cheap and there are several other amazing, high end restaurants across the road, I expected better.

Bucci has long been a family favourite & today just reaffirmed why. Few Italian restaurants can provide authentic food and flavours, with a modern, refreshing twist. Bucci is one that can and does - consistently. Always welcoming- service is friendly but not familiar. Efficient, professional and the pace is always just right. Our meals were perfectly cooked and beautifully presented. Portion sizes generous and perfect for sharing. Chef attended the table to recommend a few dishes which were outstanding. Excellent location. Love it!
Food was good and came out pretty quick. However the service was not up to par, the waiter was unfriendly and definitely not a warm welcome.

I was part of  Hen's night that recently booked out the private dining room at Bucci. We had a set menu and I was so excited to see that there were actually several options for me on it. The pasta I had was just a simple tomato and garlic sauce but it was absolutely delicious! the serving size did seem quite small for the price, however it was surprisingly filling and I am still dreaming about it. The service was very good (they were super tolerant of a bunch of loud girls) and the waiter made a note of my dietary issues and clearly passed this on to the other staff. Looking at the regular menu on their website it is a shame that they don't list what can be GF etc on the menu (other than that they offer GF pasta) so it's hard for me to get excited about visiting again and what I might order. Won't stop me coming back though!

My partner and I went to Bucci with high expectations and sadly these expectations were not met. My partner had the Bucci angnolotti which I must say was lovely. However, I had the carbonara and it was extremely salty and very disappointing. The cost of the dishes did not reflect the taste of the food we had. The service was very mediocre as we found it difficult to spot a server and grab their attention.

I could not wait to get home to review this restaurant. What a shocker. Group of 12. 2 of the people enjoyed their meal. One of the party thought their Moreton bay bug dish tasted like 2 minute noodles had as a child. My pork belly was $38. It was fatty. The crackling was soft therefore inedible (for me, others may like theirs soft). I like the crackling to be just that. crackling. 3 bites and all the meat was gone. Yes, I did ask if the chef could “crispy” up the crackling. saw this done on Masterchef by turning the skin face down onto a hot pan. took minutes. no, sorry we cannot make the skin crackling “crackly” for you. Bill was $720 for 12 . I don’t mind paying for quality so the money is not the issue, it is just that I did not receive quality. Lift your game guys, treat your customers with respect.

The food was yummy, they had a great menu with a range of different options. There was a daily specials board too. Found it to be a little pricey, so save this restaurant and visit on a special occasion :) worth a visit!

My wife and I came in on Saturday night for her work's Christmas Party. We were a little late getting in, so by the time we were seated several antipasto platters were already on the table, and the staff were quick to take ours drinks orders. There were some language barriers with one of our waiters, but he was patient with us and our drinks were brought out promptly. The antipasto platters were excellent, with just enough of everything that everybody could have a couple of bites with our drinks while we waited for mains. I had the Bucci Angolotti while my wife had the Tagliatelle Con Cicale Di Mare. While both were wonderful, my wife's gluten free replacement option for tagliatelle was box penne which was a little disappointing. For dessert we both had the Chocolate Nemesis Del "The River Cafe". What came out was a piece of cake that is taste and texture was very much like a well made brownie. I loved it immensely for it's flavor and texture and how well it went with the mascarpone. One comment made by several people at our table was that there was a tendancy for the waitstaff to hover. Attentive service is always appreciated, but it seemed like a fork or a glass couldn't be put down without somebody appearing behind us. The few cocktails we had were excellent as well. I would recommend the Amaretto Sour to anybody that way inclined, and the spirits list, while not extensive, has plenty of mid and high range options to keep spirit heads happy. The only major issue was paying. There were some drinks missing off the bill and items appearing not to be paid for when they had. It was sorted out in the end but it made the end of the night a bit of a mess. Overall though the food is lovely, the vibe is good, and the drinks are great. Happy to have been a patron to all three.

Came here last night for a glass of wine and dessert with my girlfriends. I was impressed with the wine menu and the different options. Majority of us had the flourless chocolate cake and despite the small Portion size we were all really impressed by how delicious the cake was. I will be back for sure!
I had dinner here last night and one particular waiter was awful. He was rude, aggressive at times and not helpful at all. Food was good but the service ruined it. Such a shame.
